-- ============================================================
-- Batch 22: 25 curated AI tools (Step 41 — scale to 1,500)
-- Hand-authored enrichment via parallel research. Categories targeted:
-- web hosting / domains, webinar platforms, site builders, AI portrait,
-- HR/recruiting ATS, stock/asset libraries, customer support helpdesk.
-- All entries have a verified affiliate program and fill a category gap
-- not covered by batches 1–21. All slugs deduped vs the existing
-- 1,100-slug catalog index.
-- All website_url values are bare canonical domains — no UTM, no ref,
-- no affiliate redirector. Affiliate program metadata tracked separately
-- in RightAIChoice_Affiliate_Master.xlsx.
-- ============================================================

INSERT INTO tools (
  name, slug, tagline, description, website_url,
  pricing_type, pricing_details, skill_level, has_api, platforms,
  features, integrations, is_published,
  best_for, not_for, editorial_verdict,
  tutorial_urls, limitations, models, community_links, use_cases, our_views,
  last_verified_at
) VALUES
('Hostinger', 'hostinger', 'Budget-friendly shared, cloud, and VPS hosting with a built-in AI website builder, AI writer, and AI SEO assistant.', 'Hostinger is a Lithuania-founded global hosting provider that has spent the last decade aggressively undercutting the traditional shared-hosting market on price while quietly catching up on features. The 2026 product line spans shared web hosting, managed WordPress, cloud hosting, VPS, email, and a fast-growing website-builder business — all wrapped in the proprietary hPanel control surface, which is the main alternative to cPanel that most beginners actually find usable. Plans start as low as $1.99/month on long-term commitments and renew at roughly 5x that rate, which is the standard hosting-industry pricing pattern.

The AI layer is now central to the value proposition. Hostinger ships a one-prompt AI website builder (describe a business, get a launch-ready site with copy, images, and structure in under a minute), an AI writer for blog and page copy, an AI image generator, an AI blog generator, an AI SEO assistant for AI-Overview optimisation, and Hostinger Reach — an AI-driven email-marketing tool that drafts welcome, promotional, and educational campaigns from prompts. Bundled extras like free domain (annual+ plans), free SSL, weekly backups, and a Cloudflare-powered CDN come standard.

Hostinger''s position in 2026 is the value leader for beginners and small businesses worldwide. The PartnerStack-managed affiliate program pays up to 60% recurring commission and is one of the largest and highest-converting affiliate programs in the hosting category, which is why Hostinger dominates affiliate-led search results in the SMB hosting space.', 'https://www.hostinger.com', 'paid', '[{"plan":"Premium Web Hosting","price":"$2.99/mo (48-mo term)","features":["100 websites","100 GB SSD","Free domain (1 yr)","Free SSL","Weekly backups","AI website builder"]},{"plan":"Business Web Hosting","price":"$3.99/mo (48-mo term)","features":["100 websites","200 GB NVMe","Daily backups","Free CDN","WordPress AI tools","Free email"]},{"plan":"Cloud Startup","price":"$9.99/mo (48-mo term)","features":["300 websites","200 GB NVMe","3 GB RAM","Dedicated IP","Priority support"]},{"plan":"VPS KVM 2","price":"$6.99/mo (24-mo term)","features":["2 vCPU","8 GB RAM","100 GB NVMe","Full root access","Weekly backups"]}]'::jsonb, 'beginner', true, '{"web","api"}', '{"hPanel proprietary control panel","One-prompt AI website builder","AI writer for blog and page copy","AI image generator","AI SEO assistant for AI-Overview optimisation","Hostinger Reach AI email marketing","Free domain on annual+ plans","Free SSL and Cloudflare-powered CDN","LiteSpeed web servers with LSCache","One-click WordPress install with managed updates","Weekly or daily automated backups","Built-in malware scanner and patchman"}', '{"WordPress","Cloudflare","Google Workspace","Stripe","WooCommerce","PayPal","Mailchimp","Zapier","Let''s Encrypt"}', true, '{"Beginners launching their first website on a tight budget","Small business owners who want one-prompt site generation","Bloggers and side-project builders needing cheap WordPress hosting","International users wanting global data centers with multilingual support"}', '{"High-traffic enterprise sites needing dedicated infrastructure","Agencies managing 50+ client sites (Cloudways or Kinsta fit better)","Anyone who needs cPanel specifically (Hostinger uses hPanel)"}', 'The best-value entry-level hosting in 2026 — pick it when budget is the constraint and the AI builder shortcut is genuinely useful, skip it when you need true managed-WordPress performance.', '{"https://support.hostinger.com/en/"}', 'The headline pricing is intro-only — renewals jump to roughly $10–$20/month and locking in 48-month terms requires a large upfront payment. Shared-hosting performance is good for the price but noticeably slower than Kinsta or Cloudways under real WordPress load, especially with heavy plugins. AI website builder output is competent but visually generic — sites built from one prompt look like sites built from one prompt. Support is 24/7 chat but quality varies sharply by agent and time of day. Migration tooling works for most WordPress sites but breaks on complex multi-site setups.', '{}', '{"reddit_threads":[]}'::jsonb, '{"Launch a small-business WordPress site for under $50/year on a 48-month plan.","Generate a complete launch-ready website from a one-sentence business description.","Run an EU-data-resident WordPress blog with weekly backups and free SSL.","Spin up a $7/month VPS for a side-project Node.js or Python app."}', 'Sweet spot: a beginner, freelancer, or small business launching their first 1–10 websites where every dollar matters and the goal is "online and working" rather than "best-in-class performance." Hostinger''s hPanel is genuinely friendlier than cPanel for non-technical users, the AI builder collapses the awkward blank-page problem, and the bundled domain plus SSL plus email removes three line items from the typical hosting bill. For audiences in this segment, the price-to-feature ratio in 2026 is hard to beat.

Failure modes. The biggest is buying the 48-month introductory rate and being surprised when renewal lands at 5x — model the all-in cost across the full term you''ll actually stay. The second is treating Hostinger like a managed-WordPress host: it isn''t. Plugin-heavy WooCommerce stores or membership sites with real traffic will outgrow shared hosting fast and feel slow before they''re profitable. The third is using the AI website builder as a final product rather than a starting scaffold — sites need real editorial work after the initial generation to avoid looking templated.

What to pilot. Start on a 12-month Premium plan (cheaper to exit if you outgrow it), migrate one real site, and benchmark TTFB and LCP from your actual audience''s region. If pages load under 2 seconds and uptime is clean for 60 days, scale up. If performance is sluggish or you''re hitting CPU limits during traffic spikes, the next stop is Cloud Startup or a real managed-WordPress host like Kinsta.', now()),
('Bluehost', 'bluehost', 'WordPress.org-recommended shared hosting with an AI site creator that builds a launch-ready WordPress site from one prompt.', 'Bluehost is one of the three hosts officially recommended by WordPress.org and has been since 2005, which is the single most durable distribution moat in the shared-hosting industry — millions of first-time WordPress users land on Bluehost via that recommendation each year. Owned by Newfold Digital (formerly Endurance International Group / EIG), Bluehost is a US-based provider with global data centers and the standard cPanel control surface, focused squarely on the WordPress beginner and small-business market.

The 2024–2026 product line layered AI throughout the WordPress experience. The AI Site Creator takes a one-sentence business description and generates a complete, launch-ready WordPress site — pages, copy, images, and SEO metadata — in under 60 seconds, on top of a real WordPress installation rather than a proprietary builder. Bluehost also bundles AI content tools inside WordPress for ongoing copy generation, automated WordPress core and plugin updates, free SSL, free CDN, and a free domain for the first year. The Cloud and Pro tiers add NVMe storage, malware scanning, and priority support.

Bluehost''s position in 2026 is the default starter host for WordPress beginners thanks to the WordPress.org recommendation. The in-house affiliate program pays $65–$130 per qualifying sale (varies by tier) and is one of the most-recommended hosts in WordPress-tutorial content because of that flat-fee structure, even though the per-sale economics matter less than the steady conversion volume the WordPress.org placement drives.', 'https://www.bluehost.com', 'paid', '[{"plan":"Basic","price":"$1.99/mo (36-mo intro)","features":["10 websites","10 GB NVMe","Free domain (1 yr)","Free SSL","AI Site Creator","Custom WordPress themes"]},{"plan":"Choice Plus","price":"$3.99/mo (36-mo intro)","features":["Unlimited websites","40 GB NVMe","Free CDN","Free domain privacy","Daily backups (1 yr)"]},{"plan":"Online Store","price":"$6.99/mo (36-mo intro)","features":["WooCommerce pre-installed","100 GB NVMe","Store analytics","Exclusive store themes"]},{"plan":"Pro","price":"$13.99/mo (36-mo intro)","features":["Unlimited websites","100 GB NVMe","Dedicated IP","Daily backups","Malware scanning"]}]'::jsonb, 'beginner', false, '{"web"}', '{"AI Site Creator (one-prompt WordPress site generation)","WordPress.org-recommended host since 2005","One-click WordPress install with auto-updates","Free domain for first year","Free SSL via Let''s Encrypt","Free Cloudflare CDN","cPanel control surface","WooCommerce pre-installed on Online Store tier","Daily automated backups (Choice Plus and above)","Malware scanning (Pro tier)","24/7 phone, chat, and ticket support","Built-in AI content tools inside WordPress"}', '{"WordPress","WooCommerce","Cloudflare","Let''s Encrypt","Yoast SEO","Jetpack","PayPal","Stripe","MOJO Marketplace"}', true, '{"WordPress beginners arriving from the WordPress.org recommendation","Small businesses launching a first marketing site or blog","WooCommerce stores starting under $100K/year revenue","Affiliate marketers and bloggers wanting a cheap entry point"}', '{"High-traffic WooCommerce stores past 50K visits/month (Kinsta or Cloudways win)","Developers needing SSH, Git, or staging on cheap tiers","Non-WordPress stacks (Bluehost is WordPress-first)"}', 'The default WordPress beginner host because of the WordPress.org recommendation — pick it for the easy on-ramp, plan to outgrow it once traffic gets real.', '{"https://www.bluehost.com/help"}', 'Renewal pricing roughly triples the introductory rate — the $1.99/mo Basic plan renews at $9.99/mo, and that pattern holds across every tier. Performance under WordPress load is mid-pack at best; plugin-heavy or media-rich sites slow down well before traffic gets impressive. Customer support quality has been criticized in WordPress-community forums since the EIG/Newfold acquisition era — wait times are real and resolution depth varies. Daily backups are only included free for the first year on Choice Plus and require a paid add-on after. The AI Site Creator output is on real WordPress, which is a genuine advantage, but the generated content still needs editorial polishing.', '{}', '{"reddit_threads":[]}'::jsonb, '{"Generate a small-business WordPress site from a one-sentence prompt in under a minute.","Launch a first WooCommerce store on the Online Store plan with WooCommerce pre-installed.","Run a personal blog on Basic for under $25/year (intro term) including domain.","Migrate a small WordPress site from another host using the bundled migration tooling."}', 'Sweet spot: a true WordPress beginner who arrived via the WordPress.org "recommended hosts" page, doesn''t want to research the hosting market, and just needs to ship a small site cheaply. Bluehost makes that path frictionless — the AI Site Creator removes the blank-page problem, the WordPress install is real (not a walled garden), and the support is 24/7 even if quality varies. For under-100-visits/day brochure sites and starter blogs, Bluehost is genuinely fine.

Failure modes. The biggest is staying on Bluehost too long. Once traffic crosses roughly 25K visits/month or you add WooCommerce with real catalog depth, performance and support quality stop being adequate, and the upgrade path inside Newfold Digital (Bluehost Cloud, dedicated, etc.) doesn''t close the gap with Kinsta or Cloudways. The second is buying the 36-month intro and forgetting the renewal cliff — it always lands harder than expected. The third is using the AI Site Creator as a finished product; the bones are real WordPress, but the content needs human editing.

What to pilot. Buy the 12-month Basic plan (not 36) for the lower commitment, migrate one real site, and watch TTFB, uptime, and support response time over 60 days. If the site is small and stays under 10K visits/month, Bluehost is good enough indefinitely. If you cross 25K visits or add WooCommerce with real revenue, plan the migration to Cloudways or Kinsta before the next renewal hits.', now()),
('Namecheap', 'namecheap', 'Budget domain registrar plus shared, managed WordPress (EasyWP), email, SSL, and privacy services under one account.', 'Namecheap started in 2000 as a domain registrar built around two simple opinions: cheaper renewal pricing than GoDaddy and free WHOIS privacy on every domain, both of which were industry firsts at the time. Twenty-five years later it remains one of the largest independent registrars in the world, with roughly 17 million domains under management, and has expanded into a full small-business stack: shared hosting, managed WordPress (EasyWP), private email, SSL certificates, VPN, logo maker, and a website builder.

The hosting product line has three tiers — Stellar shared hosting (cPanel-based, $1.98/month intro on Stellar Plus), EasyWP managed WordPress (proprietary cloud platform starting around $9.88/month with Turbo at $13.88/month and Supersonic at $20.88/month), and VPS / dedicated for advanced users. EasyWP is positioned as the differentiated piece: it''s a fully managed WordPress experience with NVMe storage, free SSL, free CDN, automatic updates, and unlimited monthly visitors, sitting between Bluehost-style shared WordPress and Kinsta-class premium managed hosting on the price-performance curve.

Namecheap''s position in 2026 is the value-conscious all-rounder for solo operators and small businesses who want one provider for domain, hosting, email, and SSL without paying enterprise prices. The in-house affiliate program pays competitive commissions and Namecheap regularly ranks in the top tier of registrar affiliate revenue because the brand''s long history and trusted-pricing reputation drive high conversion rates.', 'https://www.namecheap.com', 'paid', '[{"plan":"Stellar Shared Hosting","price":"$1.98/mo (intro)","features":["3 websites","20 GB SSD","Free domain","Free SSL (1 yr)","Twice-weekly backups","cPanel"]},{"plan":"EasyWP Starter","price":"$9.88/mo","features":["1 WordPress site","10 GB NVMe","Unlimited visitors","Free CDN","Auto WordPress updates"]},{"plan":"EasyWP Turbo","price":"$13.88/mo","features":["1 WordPress site","50 GB NVMe","3x faster than Starter","Free SSL","Free CDN"]},{"plan":"EasyWP Supersonic","price":"$20.88/mo","features":["1 WordPress site","100 GB NVMe","5x faster than Starter","Premium support","Free SSL"]}]'::jsonb, 'beginner', true, '{"web","api"}', '{"Domain registration with free WHOIS privacy on every TLD","EasyWP managed WordPress on a proprietary cloud platform","NVMe SSD storage on all EasyWP tiers","Free SSL via PositiveSSL or Let''s Encrypt","Built-in CDN on EasyWP plans","Automatic WordPress core and plugin updates","Private Email service with spam filtering","cPanel control surface on Stellar shared hosting","DNS management with FreeDNS","Logo maker and basic website builder","SSL certificate marketplace","VPN add-on (FastVPN)"}', '{"WordPress","Cloudflare","Let''s Encrypt","PositiveSSL","Sectigo","Stripe","PayPal","Google Workspace","Microsoft 365"}', true, '{"Solo operators consolidating domain plus hosting plus email under one bill","Small businesses needing cheap managed WordPress without renewal-cliff surprises","Side-project builders running a single WordPress site on EasyWP","Anyone shopping for the cheapest reputable domain registrar in 2026"}', '{"High-traffic WooCommerce stores or membership sites","Agencies managing 20+ client sites on one account","Developers needing SSH, Git, or staging on EasyWP (use Cloudways or Kinsta)"}', 'The best registrar-plus-budget-WordPress combo in 2026 — pick it when you want one provider for domain, email, and a managed WordPress site without paying premium prices.', '{"https://www.namecheap.com/support/"}', 'EasyWP is genuinely managed but the developer experience is thin — no SSH, no Git, no real staging environment, and limited control over PHP workers and caching layers. Stellar shared hosting performance is mid-pack; sites with heavy plugins feel sluggish. Email deliverability on Private Email is fine for transactional use but lower-volume than Google Workspace. Renewal pricing on domains is fair (Namecheap''s historical strength) but hosting renewals follow the standard intro-then-jump pattern. Support is responsive but resolution depth on complex WordPress issues is shallower than Kinsta-tier managed hosts.', '{}', '{"reddit_threads":[]}'::jsonb, '{"Register a domain with free WHOIS privacy and point it at EasyWP for a single WordPress site.","Run a small-business WordPress blog on EasyWP Starter for under $120/year.","Consolidate domain, email, and hosting under one Namecheap account to simplify renewals.","Issue a multi-domain SSL certificate from Namecheap''s SSL marketplace at registrar pricing."}', 'Sweet spot: a solo operator, freelancer, or small business that wants one trusted provider for domain, hosting, email, and SSL without negotiating enterprise pricing or stitching together five vendors. Namecheap''s consolidated billing, transparent renewal pricing on domains, and EasyWP''s genuinely managed (if developer-thin) WordPress experience cover that profile cleanly. The free WHOIS privacy on every domain remains a real cost saving versus registrars that still charge for it.

Failure modes. The biggest is treating EasyWP like Kinsta — it isn''t. There''s no SSH, no Git, no real staging, and the underlying platform isn''t tuned for plugin-heavy WooCommerce stores. Developers will hit walls fast. The second is using Stellar shared hosting for anything beyond a simple brochure site; performance degrades quickly under real traffic. The third is assuming Private Email replaces Google Workspace for client-facing teams — it works for transactional and low-volume use, not for sales teams sending hundreds of emails daily.

What to pilot. If you only need a domain, just buy it — Namecheap is reliably cheap and the free WHOIS privacy is real. If you need WordPress hosting, run EasyWP Starter for 60 days with one real site, watch TTFB and uptime, and assess whether the lack of SSH/Git/staging matters for your workflow. If it doesn''t, the price-to-value is excellent. If you find yourself needing developer features, jump straight to Cloudways or Kinsta rather than upgrading within EasyWP.', now()),
('Kinsta', 'kinsta', 'Premium managed WordPress, application, and database hosting on Google Cloud C2 with Cloudflare Enterprise CDN.', 'Kinsta is the premium managed hosting provider that defined the modern "WordPress on Google Cloud" category — every site runs on Google Cloud Platform''s C2 (compute-optimised) machines, every plan ships with Cloudflare Enterprise CDN and DDoS protection, and the MyKinsta control panel replaces cPanel with a developer-friendly dashboard built around staging, SSH, Git, WP-CLI, and per-site analytics. Founded in 2013, Kinsta has spent a decade building a reputation for performance, support, and uptime that justifies its position at the top of the managed-WordPress price ladder.

The 2024–2026 product line expanded well beyond WordPress. Application Hosting runs Node.js, Python, Ruby, PHP, Java, Go, Scala, and static-site frameworks on the same Google Cloud infrastructure with Git-driven deploys. Database Hosting runs managed MySQL, PostgreSQL, MariaDB, and Redis instances. Static Site Hosting is free for up to 100 sites with global CDN. The combined offering positions Kinsta as a Vercel-plus-WP-Engine hybrid: managed WordPress for the marketing site, application hosting for the SaaS app, database hosting for the backend, all under one bill with one support team.

Kinsta''s position in 2026 is the premium choice for businesses where uptime, performance, and support quality justify paying 5–10x what shared hosting costs. The PartnerStack-managed affiliate program pays $50–$500 per referral plus 10% recurring commission, and Kinsta is one of the most-recommended hosts in WordPress-developer circles because the support and infrastructure quality genuinely show up in reviews.', 'https://kinsta.com', 'paid', '[{"plan":"Starter","price":"$35/mo","features":["1 WordPress site","25K monthly visits","10 GB storage","Free Cloudflare Enterprise CDN","Free SSL","Daily backups"]},{"plan":"Pro","price":"$70/mo","features":["2 WordPress sites","50K monthly visits","20 GB storage","Free site migrations","Staging environments"]},{"plan":"Business 1","price":"$115/mo","features":["5 WordPress sites","100K monthly visits","30 GB storage","Edge caching","APM tool"]},{"plan":"Enterprise","price":"From $675/mo","features":["60+ sites","1M+ monthly visits","Hourly backups","Premium support","Dedicated account manager"]}]'::jsonb, 'intermediate', true, '{"web","api"}', '{"Google Cloud Platform C2 (compute-optimised) machines","Cloudflare Enterprise CDN and DDoS protection on every plan","MyKinsta proprietary control panel (no cPanel)","SSH, Git, WP-CLI, and Composer access on every plan","Free site migrations performed by Kinsta engineers","One-click staging environments","Application Performance Monitoring (APM) built in","Application Hosting (Node, Python, Ruby, PHP, Java, Go)","Database Hosting (MySQL, PostgreSQL, MariaDB, Redis)","Static Site Hosting (free for up to 100 sites)","Edge caching across 35+ data centers","24/7 expert WordPress support with avg <2-min response"}', '{"Google Cloud","Cloudflare","WordPress","WooCommerce","GitHub","GitLab","Bitbucket","Stripe","Slack","Let''s Encrypt"}', true, '{"Mid-market businesses where downtime costs more than hosting","WooCommerce stores past 25K visits/month needing real performance","Agencies managing 5–60 client WordPress sites","SaaS teams running app, database, and marketing site under one provider"}', '{"Hobby projects and personal blogs (overpriced for low traffic)","Beginners who want one-click everything (MyKinsta has a learning curve)","Buyers shopping purely on price (Hostinger and Namecheap are 5–10x cheaper)"}', 'The premium managed-WordPress benchmark in 2026 — pick Kinsta when performance, uptime, and support quality matter more than the bill, skip it for hobby sites or when budget is the constraint.', '{"https://kinsta.com/docs/"}', 'Pricing is materially higher than mass-market hosts — the $35/mo Starter is 10–15x what Hostinger or Namecheap charge intro, and the visit-count-based limits punish viral spikes (a single Reddit-front-page traffic event can push you up a tier mid-month). Sites are limited per plan, so agencies managing many small sites pay more than they would on a per-server provider like Cloudways. The MyKinsta panel is excellent for developers but unfamiliar to cPanel veterans. PHP-only — no Ruby, Node, or static apps on the WordPress plans (those need separate Application Hosting / Static Site Hosting subscriptions). Email hosting is not included; bring your own Google Workspace or transactional service.', '{}', '{"reddit_threads":[]}'::jsonb, '{"Run a high-traffic WooCommerce store with sub-second TTFB on Cloudflare Enterprise.","Host a Node.js SaaS app, its PostgreSQL database, and the marketing site under one Kinsta account.","Migrate a sluggish WordPress site from Bluehost and cut LCP by 40%+ with edge caching.","Manage 30 agency client sites with per-site staging, SSH, and free monthly migrations."}', 'Sweet spot: a mid-market business or agency where the WordPress site is generating real revenue and downtime, slow page loads, or support black holes cost more than $115/month per site. Kinsta''s combination of Google Cloud C2 plus Cloudflare Enterprise plus genuine WordPress-expert support is the benchmark in this segment, and the developer tooling (SSH, Git, WP-CLI, staging) means engineering teams can actually work the way they want to. The expanded Application and Database Hosting make it credible as a one-vendor stack for SaaS companies running WordPress for marketing and a real app for the product.

Failure modes. The biggest is buying Kinsta when shared hosting would do — a brochure site doing 2K visits/month is wildly overpaying at $35/mo. The second is hitting the visit-count cap during a viral moment and getting overage-billed; pay attention to the cap and pre-upgrade if you''re running a campaign. The third is treating Application Hosting like Vercel — it runs apps well but doesn''t have the same Git-push-to-preview-URL polish that Vercel and Netlify built their brands on; expect a more traditional managed-host workflow.

What to pilot. Migrate one real site (Kinsta does it free) and run it for 60 days. Measure TTFB from your audience''s primary region, monitor uptime, and time-test their support. If a real WordPress problem gets a knowledgeable response in under 5 minutes and TTFB stays under 200ms, the price is justified for any site doing meaningful revenue. If your site is small and traffic is flat, Cloudways at $14–$30/month gets you 80% of the performance for 20% of the price.', now()),
('Cloudways', 'cloudways', 'Managed cloud hosting on DigitalOcean, Vultr, Linode, AWS, and Google Cloud — one control panel across five infrastructure providers.', 'Cloudways is a managed-cloud-hosting platform (acquired by DigitalOcean in 2022) that solves a very specific problem: cloud infrastructure providers like DigitalOcean, Vultr, Linode, AWS, and Google Cloud are powerful but require Linux sysadmin skills to run a WordPress, Magento, or Laravel site on. Cloudways layers a managed control panel on top, so you pick a provider, click to spin up a server, and Cloudways handles LEMP stack provisioning, caching (Varnish, Redis, Memcached), SSL, backups, staging, and security patching. You pay Cloudways a managed-services fee on top of the underlying cloud cost, all consolidated into one bill.

The 2024–2026 product line spans WordPress (with the Breeze caching plugin and the Cloudways CDN), WooCommerce (with optimised configurations), Magento, Laravel, and any custom PHP application. Pricing starts at $11/month for DigitalOcean Standard ($14 for DigitalOcean Premium / Vultr / Linode), $20.56 for AWS, and $37.33 for Google Cloud — every plan includes unlimited applications per server, 24/7 chat support, free SSL, free migration of one site, free Object Cache Pro on higher tiers, and the same control panel regardless of underlying provider. Pay-as-you-go billing with no contracts is a real differentiator versus the 1–3-year intro contracts most shared hosts require.

Cloudways'' position in 2026 is the developer-friendly mid-tier: more flexible and faster than Bluehost / Hostinger, much cheaper than Kinsta or WP Engine, with a real cPanel-replacement experience. The PartnerStack-managed tiered affiliate program (slab-based commissions plus hybrid recurring) is widely promoted across hosting-review content because the conversion economics work at scale.', 'https://www.cloudways.com', 'paid', '[{"plan":"DigitalOcean Standard 1GB","price":"$11/mo","features":["1 GB RAM","25 GB storage","1 TB bandwidth","Unlimited applications","Free SSL","24/7 chat support"]},{"plan":"Vultr High Frequency 1GB","price":"$16/mo","features":["1 GB RAM","32 GB NVMe","2 TB bandwidth","High-frequency CPU","Free migration"]},{"plan":"Linode 1GB","price":"$14/mo","features":["1 GB RAM","25 GB storage","1 TB bandwidth","Free CDN","Staging environment"]},{"plan":"AWS Small","price":"$36.51/mo","features":["1.75 GB RAM","20 GB storage","2 GB bandwidth","Enterprise infrastructure","Premium support"]}]'::jsonb, 'intermediate', true, '{"web","api"}', '{"Managed control panel across DigitalOcean, Vultr, Linode, AWS, and GCP","Unlimited applications per server","Built-in Varnish, Redis, Memcached, and Nginx caching","Breeze WordPress caching plugin (free)","One-click staging environments","Free SSL via Let''s Encrypt","Free migration plugin (Cloudways WordPress Migrator)","Pay-as-you-go billing with no contracts","Automated backups (configurable frequency)","SSH, SFTP, Git deployment","CloudwaysCDN add-on","24/7 live chat with Linux-trained support"}', '{"DigitalOcean","Vultr","Linode","AWS","Google Cloud","Cloudflare","WordPress","WooCommerce","Magento","Laravel","Stripe","PayPal"}', true, '{"WordPress and WooCommerce sites past 10K visits/month wanting real performance","Agencies running 10–100 client sites on shared servers with isolation","Laravel and custom-PHP developers needing managed cloud infrastructure","Operators wanting Kinsta-style performance at one-third the price"}', '{"Pure beginners who want one-click everything (Bluehost or Hostinger fit better)","Hobby sites doing under 1K visits/month (Cloudways is overkill)","Teams that need cPanel specifically (Cloudways uses its own panel)"}', 'The best price-performance managed cloud host in 2026 — pick Cloudways when you''ve outgrown shared hosting but Kinsta is overkill, skip it if you need true one-click simplicity.', '{"https://support.cloudways.com/en/"}', 'The Cloudways panel is much friendlier than raw cloud-provider dashboards but still has a learning curve compared to cPanel — non-technical users will need a tutorial pass before they''re comfortable. Email hosting is not included; bring your own (Google Workspace, Rackspace, or the paid Elastic Email add-on). Smaller plans (1 GB RAM) handle modest WordPress traffic but get tight fast under WooCommerce or membership-plugin load — most real sites end up on 2 GB or 4 GB plans, which costs $26–$54/month before add-ons. Support is solid but resolution on application-level WordPress issues sometimes requires escalation. Renewal pricing matches intro pricing (no bait-and-switch), which is a real positive — but the Object Cache Pro and CDN add-ons can quietly add to the monthly bill.', '{}', '{"reddit_threads":[]}'::jsonb, '{"Move a WooCommerce store from Bluehost to a $26/mo Vultr High Frequency server and cut TTFB by 60%.","Run 25 agency client WordPress sites on a single $54/mo Vultr server with per-app isolation.","Deploy a Laravel app on DigitalOcean with Redis caching and Git-based deploys.","Spin up a staging environment for a WooCommerce store, test a major plugin update, then push to production with one click."}', 'Sweet spot: a developer, freelancer, or agency managing real WordPress, WooCommerce, or PHP sites where shared hosting has stopped performing but Kinsta-tier pricing isn''t justified. Cloudways at $14–$54/month per server gives you genuinely modern infrastructure (NVMe, Redis, Varnish, staging, SSH, Git) with a managed layer on top, and the multi-cloud choice means you''re not locked into one provider''s pricing or geography. The pay-as-you-go billing without long-term contracts is the right model for agency work where projects come and go.

Failure modes. The biggest is undersizing the server. The 1 GB RAM plans are real-cheap but real-tight — most production WordPress or WooCommerce sites need 2 GB minimum, and that doubles the monthly cost. Model your real RAM usage before committing. The second is forgetting that email is not included; teams that don''t already have Google Workspace get caught flat-footed when their domain''s email stops routing on migration day. The third is treating Cloudways like a beginner host — it isn''t, and trying to operate it without basic comfort with WordPress + a Linux-flavoured panel will produce frustration.

What to pilot. Spin up the cheapest DigitalOcean 1 GB server ($11/mo, no contract), migrate one real site using the free migration plugin, and benchmark performance for 60 days. If TTFB and LCP are materially better than your current shared host and the panel doesn''t scare you, scale up to 2–4 GB or add servers as needed. If you find yourself constantly wishing for cPanel or for someone to fix things for you, accept that Cloudways isn''t the right tier and either drop down to Bluehost or jump up to Kinsta.', now()),
('Demio', 'demio', 'Browser-based live and automated webinar platform built for marketers, with AI replays and HubSpot-grade tracking.', 'Demio is a no-download, browser-based webinar platform that has held a clear positioning since launch: solve the registration-to-replay marketing funnel without forcing attendees to install Zoom or fight a clunky GoToWebinar interface. The 2026 product covers live webinars, automated/evergreen webinars (Growth tier and up), hybrid series webinars, and on-demand replays — all behind a branded registration page, custom thank-you flow, and built-in email reminders. The AI layer added across 2024–2026 generates replay summaries, highlight clips, chapter markers, and full transcripts for SEO and lead-nurture follow-up.

The platform is owned by Banzai (NASDAQ: BNZI) and integrates deeply with the marketing stack — HubSpot, Marketo, ActiveCampaign, Mailchimp, Salesforce, Keap, Zapier — so registrations, attendance, watch percentage, and CTA clicks flow into the CRM as lead-scoring events. Engagement features inside the room (polls, handouts, featured offers, live chat moderation, Q&A prioritisation) are designed for marketing webinars rather than internal training, which is what separates Demio from Zoom Webinar in actual use.

Demio''s position in 2026 is the marketing-team default for under-1,000-attendee webinars where conversion and CRM sync matter more than mass scale. WebinarJam wins on price-per-attendee at the high end, Livestorm wins on European data residency, eWebinar wins on pure evergreen — Demio holds the middle by being the most balanced platform across live, automated, and analytics. The PartnerStack-managed affiliate program pays recurring commission on a 12-month attribution window.', 'https://demio.com', 'paid', '[{"plan":"Starter","price":"$45/mo (annual)","features":["1 host","50-attendee room","Live webinars","Branded registration","Standard integrations"]},{"plan":"Growth","price":"$75/mo (annual)","features":["150-attendee room","Multiple hosts","Automated and series webinars","Custom branding","Premium integrations"]},{"plan":"Premium","price":"From $196/mo","features":["10-hour session limit","Custom domains","Priority support","Premium integrations","Dedicated success manager"]},{"plan":"Free Trial","price":"$0","features":["14-day trial","Growth-tier features","20-attendee cap"]}]'::jsonb, 'beginner', true, '{"web","api"}', '{"Browser-based live webinars (no download for attendees)","Automated and evergreen webinars (Growth and up)","Series webinars for multi-session funnels","AI-generated replay summaries and highlight clips","Auto-generated transcripts and chapter markers","Branded registration pages and thank-you flows","Built-in email reminders and follow-up sequences","Polls, handouts, and featured offers inside the room","Live chat moderation and prioritised Q&A","Per-attendee engagement analytics","CRM sync (HubSpot, Marketo, Salesforce)","Custom domains (Premium)"}', '{"HubSpot","Marketo","ActiveCampaign","Mailchimp","Salesforce","Keap","Zapier","Drip","GoToWebinar","Webhooks"}', true, '{"B2B marketing teams running demand-gen webinars under 1,000 attendees","Course creators selling via live and automated webinar funnels","Customer marketing teams running product update sessions","Agencies running webinars for multiple clients on one platform"}', '{"Internal company all-hands and training (Zoom is cheaper)","Massive 5,000+ attendee broadcasts (WebinarJam Enterprise fits better)","Teams that don''t need CRM sync or marketing automation"}', 'The most balanced marketing-webinar platform in 2026 — pick it when you need live plus evergreen plus CRM sync in one tool, skip it if you only need internal video meetings.', '{"https://help.demio.com/"}', 'Pricing scales with both host count and room size, which gets expensive fast for a 4-host team running 500-attendee webinars — the Premium tier and overages can push past $400/month before integrations. Automated webinars are gated to the Growth tier, so the Starter plan is genuinely live-only. The browser-based architecture occasionally struggles on attendee networks below 5 Mbps and there''s no fallback dial-in option, which loses 2–4% of registrants on weak connections. AI replay summaries are competent but generic — high-stakes content needs human editing before publishing externally.', '{}', '{"reddit_threads":[]}'::jsonb, '{"Run a weekly live demo webinar with branded registration and HubSpot lead sync.","Convert a top-performing live webinar into a 24/7 evergreen funnel with simulated chat.","Host a 4-week series webinar that nurtures registrants across multiple sessions.","Generate AI replay summaries and short clips for post-webinar email and social distribution."}', 'Sweet spot: a B2B SaaS or course-creator marketing team running 2–8 webinars per month at 50–500 attendees each, where the webinar is a real revenue channel rather than a content afterthought. Demio''s value isn''t the live experience itself (Zoom is fine for that) — it''s the registration page, reminder cadence, in-room conversion mechanics, and CRM sync working as one system. Teams that just want a video conferencing URL are overpaying; teams that want webinars to drive pipeline are getting fair value.

Failure modes to know. First, the Starter tier traps you in live-only mode — if your funnel relies on evergreen replays at all, budget for Growth from day one. Second, host-count pricing punishes small teams that want multiple speakers per webinar; consolidate to a single host with co-presenters where possible. Third, the AI replay tools are useful for internal triage but the auto-generated summaries shouldn''t be sent verbatim to prospects — treat them as drafts.

What to pilot. Run two webinars on the 14-day trial — one live demo with HubSpot sync wired in, one converted to automated playback. Measure registration-to-attendance rate, attendance-to-CTA-click rate, and CTA-click-to-pipeline conversion against your current platform. If the in-room conversion mechanics lift CTA-click rate by 30%+ and the CRM sync surfaces new lead-scoring signals, the Growth tier pays for itself. If conversion is flat, the bottleneck is your webinar content, not the platform.', now()),
('Livestorm', 'livestorm', 'Browser-based webinar and virtual events platform with AI summaries, engagement tools, and GDPR-friendly EU data residency.', 'Livestorm is a Paris-headquartered webinar and virtual events platform that has held a clear lane since 2016: a fully browser-based experience for both hosts and attendees (no downloads, no installs), strong engagement mechanics (polls, Q&A, chat, emoji reactions, breakout rooms), and EU data residency that makes it the default choice for European enterprises that can''t put attendee data on US infrastructure. The 2026 product covers live webinars, on-demand and automated webinars, virtual events with multiple sessions and tracks, meetings, and product demos.

The AI layer added across 2024–2026 is now central: Livestorm AI generates session summaries, action items, transcript highlights, and short-form clips suitable for social or email follow-up. Engagement analytics flow into the marketing stack via deep integrations with HubSpot, Marketo, Pardot, and Salesforce, so attendance, watch percentage, poll responses, and Q&A activity become lead-scoring events. The contact-based pricing model (you pay for active monthly contacts, not seats) makes it predictable for marketing teams running large registration funnels.

Livestorm''s position in 2026 is the European-friendly alternative to Demio and the engagement-rich alternative to Zoom Webinar. It wins when GDPR matters, when interactive engagement (not just broadcast) is the goal, and when virtual events with multiple sessions need a single registration system. The PartnerStack-managed affiliate program is a strong fit for B2B marketing publishers and event-tech reviewers.', 'https://livestorm.co', 'freemium', '[{"plan":"Free","price":"$0","features":["30-attendee cap","20-minute session limit","Unlimited duration on platform","Basic engagement tools"]},{"plan":"Pro","price":"From $99/mo","features":["100-500 active contacts","4-hour sessions","Up to 100 attendees","CRM integrations","AI summaries"]},{"plan":"Business","price":"Custom","features":["Unlimited active contacts","Up to 3,000 live attendees","Unlimited team members","VIP support","Custom branding"]},{"plan":"Enterprise","price":"Custom","features":["12-hour sessions","3,000 live attendees","Salesforce / Marketo / Pardot","Advanced custom reporting","SSO and SAML"]}]'::jsonb, 'beginner', true, '{"web","api"}', '{"Browser-based webinars (no download required)","Live, on-demand, and automated webinar modes","Virtual events with multi-session tracks","AI-generated session summaries and action items","AI transcript highlights and short-form clips","Polls, Q&A, chat, emoji reactions, breakout rooms","Branded registration pages and email sequences","Per-attendee engagement analytics and replay tracking","CRM sync (HubSpot, Marketo, Pardot, Salesforce)","EU data residency and GDPR compliance","Custom branding and white-label options","Webhooks and REST API"}', '{"HubSpot","Marketo","Pardot","Salesforce","Mailchimp","Slack","Zapier","Make","Calendly","Eventbrite"}', true, '{"European B2B marketing teams that need GDPR-friendly data residency","Event marketing teams running multi-session virtual conferences","Customer education teams running interactive product training","Sales teams running high-engagement product demos"}', '{"Solo creators running consumer webinars (WebinarJam fits better)","Teams that need 5,000+ attendee broadcast scale","Internal company meetings and all-hands (Zoom is cheaper)"}', 'The strongest browser-based webinar platform for European and engagement-focused B2B teams in 2026 — pick it when GDPR and interactive engagement matter, skip it for pure broadcast use cases.', '{"https://support.livestorm.co/"}', 'The contact-based pricing model is predictable but punishes teams with large pre-existing CRM lists — your active contact count includes everyone who registered in the trailing month, not just attendees. The Pro tier''s 4-hour session cap is fine for most webinars but trips up multi-track virtual events that run all day; you need Enterprise for 12-hour sessions. AI summaries are useful for internal triage but produce generic copy without careful prompt customisation. Business and Enterprise pricing is opaque — expect a real sales cycle to get a quote, with annual contracts strongly preferred over monthly.', '{}', '{"reddit_threads":[]}'::jsonb, '{"Run a weekly product webinar with HubSpot sync and AI-generated post-event summary emails.","Host a multi-session virtual conference with 1,500 registrants across 8 tracks.","Convert top-performing live webinars into automated on-demand funnels for evergreen lead-gen.","Run an interactive customer training session with breakout rooms and live Q&A."}', 'Sweet spot: a European-headquartered B2B SaaS or services company running 4–20 webinars and virtual events per month, where engagement (polls, Q&A, breakouts) is part of the conversion motion and where attendee data has to stay on EU infrastructure. Livestorm''s value is the combination — most platforms get you one of those three things; Livestorm gets you all three in one bill.

Failure modes to know. First, the active-contacts pricing surprises teams whose marketing automation pumps lots of registrants who never attend; clean your registration funnel or budget for the higher tier. Second, the AI summary feature is a productivity helper, not a replacement for editorial judgement — published summaries need human editing for brand voice. Third, virtual events with complex multi-track scheduling work but the admin UI shows its age compared to dedicated event platforms like Hopin or Goldcast for very large events.

What to pilot. Run two webinars on the free or Pro trial — one standard live demo, one multi-session mini-event with two parallel tracks. Measure registration-to-attendance, engagement-action rate (polls answered, Q&A submitted), and the post-event AI summary quality against your current platform. If engagement actions lift 25%+ and the GDPR posture eliminates a compliance headache, the Pro or Business tier is justified. If engagement is flat, the bottleneck is content design, not the platform.', now()),
('WebinarJam', 'webinarjam', 'High-volume live webinar platform paired with EverWebinar for evergreen funnels — the conversion-focused choice for marketers and course creators.', 'WebinarJam is a long-running live webinar platform from Genesis Digital that has held a clear lane since 2014: maximise live attendance, in-room conversion, and post-webinar replay revenue for marketers and course creators selling high-ticket digital products. The platform is purpose-built for selling — the in-room experience includes the Active Offer system (timed pop-up offers with countdown timers), Panic Button (one-click failover to a backup webinar room if the live one breaks), Always-On Live Room (instant pre-warmed rooms for impromptu sessions), and the Control Center for managing multi-host enterprise sessions.

WebinarJam''s biggest structural advantage in 2026 is bundling: paid tiers from Basic upward include EverWebinar (the sister evergreen-webinar product) at no extra cost, which would otherwise be a separate $66–$164/month subscription. The combined stack lets teams run live launches and convert them to 24/7 automated funnels without juggling two vendors or re-recording. Live capacity scales to 5,000 concurrent attendees on the Enterprise tier, which is rare in this price range.

WebinarJam''s position in 2026 is the conversion-optimised choice for direct-response marketers, course creators, and high-ticket coaches who care less about polish and more about funnel mechanics. Demio wins on UI elegance and CRM depth, Livestorm wins on EU compliance — WebinarJam wins on raw selling features and the EverWebinar bundle. The in-house affiliate program runs through JVZoo and pays generous commission, which is why WebinarJam reviews dominate affiliate-marketing blogs.', 'https://www.webinarjam.com', 'paid', '[{"plan":"Starter","price":"$39/mo (annual)","features":["100 attendees","1 host","1-hour sessions","Live webinars only"]},{"plan":"Basic","price":"$79/mo (annual)","features":["500 attendees","2 hosts","2-hour sessions","EverWebinar included"]},{"plan":"Professional","price":"$229/mo (annual)","features":["2,000 attendees","4 hosts","3-hour sessions","Panic Button","Always-On Live Room","EverWebinar included"]},{"plan":"Enterprise","price":"$379/mo (annual)","features":["5,000 attendees","6 hosts","4-hour sessions","Control Center","Panic Button","Always-On Live Room","EverWebinar included"]}]'::jsonb, 'intermediate', false, '{"web"}', '{"Live webinars up to 5,000 concurrent attendees","EverWebinar evergreen automated webinars (bundled from Basic)","Active Offer system with countdown timers","Panic Button — one-click failover to backup room","Always-On Live Room for instant pre-warmed sessions","Control Center for multi-host management (Enterprise)","Polls, surveys, and live Q&A","Branded registration pages and email reminders","Live chat moderation and private comments","Replay rooms with engagement tracking","Pop-up offers and CTAs inside the room","Multiple-host streaming (up to 6 on Enterprise)"}', '{"Mailchimp","ActiveCampaign","ConvertKit","Keap","Aweber","GetResponse","HubSpot","Drip","Zapier","Ontraport"}', true, '{"Course creators running high-ticket launch webinars","Direct-response marketers selling info products","High-ticket coaches running weekly sales webinars","Affiliate marketers wanting JVZoo-friendly attribution"}', '{"Enterprise B2B marketing teams that need polished UX (Demio fits better)","European teams with strict GDPR data residency requirements","Internal training and corporate communications use cases"}', 'The conversion-focused choice for direct-response webinar marketers in 2026 — pick it for selling-focused funnels with EverWebinar bundled, skip it for polished B2B brand experiences.', '{"https://genesisdigital.zendesk.com/"}', 'No monthly billing — annual pricing only, which is a real commitment if you''re still validating the channel; the $1 14-day Basic trial is the only escape hatch. The UI is functional but dated compared to Demio and Livestorm; non-technical operators need real onboarding time. No native API, which limits programmatic integration — most data flows happen through Zapier and email-marketing webhooks. Replay analytics are thinner than Demio or Wistia, and there''s no AI replay summarisation built in. The platform also has occasional issues with delivery on weak attendee networks under 3 Mbps with no dial-in fallback.', '{}', '{"reddit_threads":[]}'::jsonb, '{"Run a weekly $2K+ course-launch webinar with timed Active Offers and countdown timers.","Convert top-performing live launches into 24/7 EverWebinar funnels without re-recording.","Host a 2,000-attendee high-ticket coaching pitch with simulated live engagement.","Run failover-protected high-stakes webinars using the Panic Button safety net."}', 'Sweet spot: a course creator, high-ticket coach, or direct-response marketer running monthly or weekly conversion-focused webinars where the goal is closing $500–$5,000+ digital products on the call. The bundled EverWebinar and the Active Offer mechanics are genuinely valuable for that motion — most other platforms charge separately for evergreen and don''t have the same in-room selling toolkit. Teams whose webinars are pure brand or education are overpaying for features they won''t use.

Failure modes. First, annual-only billing means a wrong-fit purchase costs a full year unless you catch it inside the 30-day refund window. Run the $1 trial seriously before committing. Second, the UI''s dated design occasionally makes registration pages look less professional than Demio''s — high-end B2B brands sometimes find this off-brand. Third, EverWebinar''s simulated-chat feature is a conversion lever but also a credibility risk if attendees notice the pre-scheduled comments — calibrate the simulation density carefully.

What to pilot. On the $1 Basic trial, run one live launch webinar end-to-end (registration page, reminder sequence, live session with Active Offers, replay room) and measure registration-to-attendance, attendance-to-offer-view, and offer-view-to-purchase rates. If the in-room selling features lift offer-view-to-purchase by 30%+ versus your current platform, the annual commitment pays for itself in one launch. If lift is marginal, the bottleneck is your offer or pitch, not the platform.', now()),
('Restream', 'restream', 'Multi-platform livestreaming, Restream Studio, and AI subtitles — the default tool for streaming to YouTube, LinkedIn, X, Twitch, and Facebook simultaneously.', 'Restream is the dominant multi-platform livestreaming tool — the service that lets a creator, brand, or marketer go live on YouTube, LinkedIn, X, Twitch, Facebook, Kick, and 30+ other destinations simultaneously from a single dashboard. The 2026 product line covers three pillars: classic multistreaming (route a single RTMP stream to multiple destinations), Restream Studio (browser-based virtual studio for guest interviews, on-screen graphics, screen sharing, and pre-recorded clip rolls), and Restream Events (scheduled live events with branded landing pages and registration flows).

The AI layer added across 2024–2026 includes auto-generated subtitles in 30+ languages (live and post-stream), AI-generated short clips suitable for Reels / Shorts / TikTok from longer streams, AI-generated stream descriptions and titles for SEO, and live caption translation. The platform also publishes pre-recorded video on a schedule (Studio + Storage), which is popular with podcasters who want to "go live" with a pre-edited episode.

Restream''s position in 2026 is the default for anyone whose strategy involves "be live in multiple places at once." StreamYard competes hard on Studio polish, OBS plus Restream is still the power-user combination, but Restream owns the easy multistream-plus-studio bundle. The in-house affiliate program pays recurring commission and is widely promoted in creator-economy channels.', 'https://restream.io', 'freemium', '[{"plan":"Free","price":"$0","features":["2 channels","720p","Restream watermark","Basic Studio access"]},{"plan":"Standard","price":"$16/mo (annual)","features":["3 channels","No watermark","Custom graphics","Restream Studio"]},{"plan":"Professional","price":"$39/mo (annual)","features":["5 channels","1080p streaming","Team access","Split recordings","Pre-recorded video upload"]},{"plan":"Business","price":"$199/mo (annual)","features":["8 channels","SRT ingest","Web player","Priority support","Restream Events"]}]'::jsonb, 'beginner', true, '{"web","api"}', '{"Multistream to 30+ platforms simultaneously","Restream Studio — browser-based virtual studio","On-screen graphics, lower thirds, and overlays","Guest interviews via shareable join links","AI-generated live subtitles (30+ languages)","AI-generated short clips for Reels / Shorts / TikTok","AI-generated stream titles and descriptions","Pre-recorded video scheduling and upload","Restream Events with branded landing pages","SRT ingest for professional encoders (Business)","Split recordings per guest","Cloud storage for past streams"}', '{"YouTube","LinkedIn","X","Twitch","Facebook","Kick","TikTok","OBS Studio","Streamlabs","Zapier"}', true, '{"Creators streaming simultaneously to YouTube plus LinkedIn plus X","Podcasters running live video episodes with multiple guests","Brands running multi-platform product launches","Agencies streaming client events to multiple destinations"}', '{"Single-platform streamers who don''t need multistream (StreamYard or native is fine)","Enterprise broadcast operations (Vimeo Livestream / IBM fit better)","Teams running pure private internal webinars"}', 'The default multi-platform livestreaming tool in 2026 — pick it when you stream to 3+ destinations at once, skip it if you only stream to one platform.', '{"https://support.restream.io/"}', 'The Free tier carries a Restream watermark that''s prominent enough to be a credibility issue for brand streams — Standard is effectively the real entry point. Multistreaming is reliable but requires solid upload bandwidth (5+ Mbps minimum, 15+ for 1080p with multiple destinations); weak networks cause dropped frames on individual destinations without a clear failure signal. AI clips are useful for first drafts but the auto-detected highlights miss context — manual selection still beats the AI for high-stakes content. Channels are gated tightly per tier, so the jump from Standard (3) to Professional (5) to Business (8) costs real money once you outgrow Standard.', '{}', '{"reddit_threads":[]}'::jsonb, '{"Stream a weekly podcast simultaneously to YouTube, LinkedIn, X, and Spotify Greenroom.","Run a multi-guest interview show in Restream Studio with on-screen graphics and lower thirds.","Generate post-stream short-form clips automatically for Reels, Shorts, and TikTok distribution.","Run a Restream Events product-launch broadcast with branded registration page and post-event replay."}', 'Sweet spot: a creator, podcaster, or brand whose livestream strategy requires being on 3+ platforms simultaneously, and who wants Studio-grade polish (graphics, guests, branding) without setting up OBS plus a dedicated multistream service. Restream''s value is the bundle — Studio plus multistream plus AI clips plus Events under one bill replaces what would otherwise be Riverside or StreamYard plus a separate multistream layer plus a separate clip tool.

Failure modes to know. First, the Free tier''s watermark and 720p cap are too restrictive for any real brand presence — Standard is the practical floor. Second, AI clip detection works well on conversational content (podcasts, interviews) but poorly on monologue or screen-share streams where there''s no clear emotional inflection — set expectations accordingly. Third, the channel limits force trade-offs: a Business-tier $199/month commitment is the only path to 8-channel multistreaming, which is expensive if you''re only doing it occasionally.

What to pilot. Run four streams across two weeks on the Standard or Professional plan — two solo monologue, two with guests via Studio. Measure dropped-frame rate per destination, AI clip quality (subjectively, on a 1-5 scale), and the time saved versus your current setup. If multistream stability is high and the time savings are real, the per-month cost is justified. If you''re only ever streaming to one platform, you''re paying for capability you don''t need — go native.', now()),
('eWebinar', 'ewebinar', 'Automated and evergreen webinar platform with live chat takeover — the dedicated tool for running pre-recorded webinars 24/7.', 'eWebinar is a Vancouver-based platform that has held a tightly focused position since launch: do one thing — automated and evergreen webinars — better than the live-first incumbents that bolt on automation as an afterthought. The product takes a pre-recorded video (your existing webinar, demo, or training session), wraps it in a scheduled or on-demand registration flow, and plays it back as if it were live, complete with simulated chat, polls, handouts, CTAs, and timed Q&A. The signature differentiator is live chat takeover: a real human can jump into any "live" replay session in real time when an attendee asks a question, blending automation efficiency with personal touch.

The platform is built for SaaS onboarding, customer training, evergreen marketing funnels, and continuous product demos — use cases where the same content needs to be delivered consistently to hundreds or thousands of viewers without a host running each session. Engagement features (polls, exit surveys, gated CTAs, downloadable handouts) trigger at exact timestamps in the recording, and post-webinar follow-up emails segment by completion percentage and engagement actions. eWebinar integrates with HubSpot, Salesforce, Mailchimp, ActiveCampaign, Pipedrive, Zapier, and most SaaS-stack staples.

eWebinar''s position in 2026 is the dedicated automated-webinar specialist. EverWebinar is the bundled-with-WebinarJam alternative; Demio and Livestorm offer evergreen as a side feature; eWebinar is the only platform whose entire product is automated webinars, which is what gets it picked when automation is the core requirement, not a nice-to-have. The in-house affiliate program pays recurring commission.', 'https://ewebinar.com', 'paid', '[{"plan":"Free Trial","price":"$0","features":["14-day trial","Full feature access","No credit card required","No permanent free plan"]},{"plan":"Level 1","price":"$99/mo","features":["1 published webinar","Unlimited registrants","Live chat takeover","All integrations","Custom branding"]},{"plan":"Level 2 (Growth)","price":"$199/mo","features":["5 published webinars","Unlimited registrants","Live chat takeover","All integrations","Priority support"]},{"plan":"Level 3","price":"$299/mo","features":["Unlimited published webinars","Unlimited registrants","All features","Priority support","Annual billing saves ~20%"]}]'::jsonb, 'beginner', true, '{"web","api"}', '{"Pre-recorded webinars played as scheduled or on-demand","Live chat takeover — real humans jump into automated sessions","Simulated live chat with timed comments","Timed polls, handouts, and CTAs at exact timestamps","Post-webinar follow-up emails segmented by engagement","Branded registration pages and reminder sequences","Just-in-time scheduling (next session within minutes)","Engagement analytics with watch percentage per attendee","Multi-language interface for international viewers","Embed webinars on your own domain","CRM and email-tool sync","REST API and webhooks"}', '{"HubSpot","Salesforce","Mailchimp","ActiveCampaign","Pipedrive","Intercom","Drip","Slack","Zapier","Webhooks"}', true, '{"SaaS teams running 24/7 product onboarding webinars","Course creators selling via evergreen automated funnels","Customer education teams running on-demand training libraries","Marketing teams scaling top-performing live webinars to 24/7"}', '{"Live event hosts who need real-time presenting (WebinarJam fits better)","Teams running internal company meetings","One-off webinar use cases where automation isn''t worth the setup"}', 'The dedicated automated-webinar platform in 2026 — pick it when evergreen is your primary use case, skip it if you''re running mostly live events.', '{"https://help.ewebinar.com/"}', 'No permanent free plan — every account converts to paid after the 14-day trial, even with zero active webinars (you''re billed at Level 1 minimum until cancellation). Pricing scales by published-webinar count, which makes large content libraries expensive (Level 3 unlimited at $299/month is the only scale-friendly option). Live chat takeover is the differentiator but requires a human to actually monitor — most teams underestimate the staffing required for true real-time response across multiple time zones. The platform is automation-only, so it can''t replace your live webinar tool — it''s a complement, not a substitute. Branding customisation is solid but not as deep as Demio or Livestorm for high-end B2B brand requirements.', '{}', '{"reddit_threads":[]}'::jsonb, '{"Run a 24/7 SaaS product onboarding webinar that scales to 1,000+ new users per month.","Convert a top-performing live launch webinar into an evergreen funnel with simulated chat.","Build an on-demand customer training library with 10+ topic-specific automated sessions.","Run a just-in-time demo where prospects can join a session starting within 5 minutes of registering."}', 'Sweet spot: a SaaS company, course creator, or customer education team where the same webinar content needs to be delivered to hundreds or thousands of attendees per month without a human host running each session. eWebinar''s value is automation depth — most platforms get evergreen 70% right; eWebinar gets it 95% right because it''s the only thing they build for. The live chat takeover specifically is unique enough to justify the per-month cost when even 10% of attendees ask real questions during sessions.

Failure modes to know. First, the no-permanent-free-plan billing model surprises trial users — set a calendar reminder before day 14 if you''re not committing. Second, live chat takeover sounds magical in demos but only delivers value if you actually have someone monitoring; without staffing, it''s just expensive automation. Third, the per-published-webinar pricing punishes content libraries — if you have 8+ webinars, jump to Level 3 immediately rather than upgrading repeatedly.

What to pilot. Take one underperforming live webinar replay (one that gets watched but doesn''t convert) and rebuild it as an eWebinar evergreen session with timed polls, CTAs, and live chat takeover staffed for the first two weeks. Measure attendance, completion rate, CTA click rate, and post-session conversion against the live-replay baseline over 30 days. If the engagement mechanics lift completion rate by 25%+ and CTA-click rate by 50%+, the platform pays for itself across the rest of your library. If lift is marginal, the bottleneck is the underlying content, not automation.', now()),
('Wix', 'wix', 'Drag-and-drop website builder with Wix Studio, AI Site Generator, and an integrated app market for any small business.', 'Wix is the largest consumer-and-SMB website builder in the market with 200M+ users globally, built around a fully visual drag-and-drop editor and a parallel professional-tier product called Wix Studio aimed at agencies and freelancers. The 2024–2026 product layers AI throughout — the Wix AI Site Generator (now part of Wix Harmony) builds a complete branded site from a chat conversation about the user''s business, AI text and image generators populate copy and visuals, and AI tools handle SEO meta, alt text, and section suggestions inside the editor. Unlike most competitors, Wix bundles AI features into every plan including the free tier rather than gating them behind upsells.

Beyond the core editor, Wix bundles a deep stack: Wix Stores (full e-commerce with inventory, multi-channel sales, abandoned-cart), Wix Bookings (appointments and classes), Wix Restaurants, Wix Hotels, Wix Events, Wix Blog, and a 500+ app marketplace for everything else. The 2026 pricing structure runs Light ($17/mo) for simple sites without commerce, Core ($29/mo) as the entry e-commerce plan, Business ($36/mo) for growing online stores, and Business Elite ($159/mo) for high-volume sellers, alongside an Enterprise tier.

Wix''s position in 2026 is the broadest no-code site builder for SMBs and service businesses that want visual control without learning Webflow. Squarespace owns design-led portfolios; Shopify owns serious e-commerce; Wix owns the long tail of small businesses that need a real website plus booking, blog, store, and forms in one place. Distribution runs through both an Impact-managed affiliate program and an in-house referral track.', 'https://www.wix.com', 'freemium', '[{"plan":"Free","price":"$0","features":["Wix branding and ads","500MB storage","Wix subdomain","AI Site Generator (Wix Harmony)"]},{"plan":"Light","price":"$17/mo","features":["Custom domain","Ad-free","2GB storage","Basic site (no e-commerce)"]},{"plan":"Core","price":"$29/mo","features":["E-commerce up to 50K products","Basic marketing suite","50GB storage","Loyalty programs"]},{"plan":"Business","price":"$36/mo","features":["100GB storage","10 collaborators","Complete e-commerce","Advanced marketing"]},{"plan":"Business Elite","price":"$159/mo","features":["Unlimited storage","Unlimited video hours","Priority support","High-volume e-commerce"]}]'::jsonb, 'beginner', true, '{"web","mobile","api"}', '{"Drag-and-drop visual editor","Wix AI Site Generator (Harmony) — full site from chat","AI text, image, and SEO generators","Wix Studio for agencies and freelancers","Wix Stores e-commerce with multi-channel sales","Wix Bookings (appointments and classes)","500+ app marketplace","Built-in blog with AI assistance","Custom domain and email","Mobile editor and Wix mobile apps","SEO toolkit with AI meta generation","Velo developer platform for custom code"}', '{"Stripe","PayPal","Google Analytics","Mailchimp","HubSpot","Shopify","QuickBooks","Zapier","Meta Pixel","Klaviyo"}', true, '{"Small businesses needing site plus bookings plus blog in one tool","Service businesses (salons, gyms, restaurants) using Wix Bookings","Solopreneurs launching their first online presence with AI assistance","Agencies building client sites at scale with Wix Studio"}', '{"Serious e-commerce operators (Shopify wins on scale)","Brand-design-led portfolio sites (Squarespace fits better)","Teams needing fully open-source code ownership"}', 'The broadest SMB website builder in 2026 with AI baked into every plan — pick Wix when you need a site plus bookings plus store in one bill, skip it when pure design or pure e-commerce dominates your needs.', '{"https://support.wix.com/"}', 'Once you pick a template, you cannot switch to another template without rebuilding — locks design decisions early. Site speed and Core Web Vitals lag Webflow and hand-coded competitors, particularly on image-heavy templates. SEO has improved significantly post-2020 but still lags purpose-built CMS systems on technical control. Plan caps on storage and video hours bite faster than the headline pricing suggests, particularly on Light and Core. The app marketplace is broad but quality varies — many apps carry their own per-month subscription fees on top of the Wix plan.', '{}', '{"reddit_threads":[]}'::jsonb, '{"Launch a service business website with online booking and Stripe payments in a weekend.","Build a 50-product Wix Stores shop with inventory sync to Instagram and Facebook.","Generate a complete branded site via Wix Harmony chat in under 30 minutes.","Run an agency producing 10+ client sites per quarter on Wix Studio."}', 'Sweet spot: a small service business or first-time site owner who values visual control and an all-in-one bundle (site, booking, store, blog, forms) over best-in-class anything. Wix at $29-$36/month replaces what would otherwise be three or four separate subscriptions for the typical SMB, and the Harmony AI Site Generator makes the cold-start problem (blank page paralysis) much smaller for non-designers. Wix Studio extends the same value to agencies running multiple client sites.

Failure modes. First, the template lock-in is real — choose carefully because switching means rebuilding the whole site. Second, Wix is rarely the right answer at the high end of e-commerce: once you cross 1,000 SKUs or need serious headless flexibility, Shopify or BigCommerce will out-perform on every dimension that matters. Third, performance on image-heavy templates can dent SEO and conversion; aggressive image optimisation and minimal third-party apps are required to keep Lighthouse scores respectable. Fourth, the app marketplace add-on costs compound monthly bills quickly if you''re not disciplined.

What to pilot. Use the free tier to generate a site via Harmony, swap in your real copy and images, wire up Wix Bookings or Wix Stores depending on your model, and stress-test mobile speed and checkout. If the AI-generated structure feels close to right and the bundled features cover 80%+ of your stack, the Light or Core plan is a fast yes. If you find yourself reaching for paid apps for every feature, reconsider — the all-in cost stops being competitive once add-ons stack up.', now()),
('Squarespace', 'squarespace', 'Template-driven website builder with commerce, scheduling via Acuity, and the Design Intelligence AI suite for brand-led sites.', 'Squarespace is the design-forward website builder of choice for creatives, brands, and small businesses that prioritise typography, layout, and editorial polish over maximum customisation. The 2024–2026 product is structured around four website plans — Basic ($16/mo), Core ($23/mo), Plus ($39/mo), and Advanced ($99/mo) — that replaced the older Personal/Business/Commerce naming, plus separate Acuity Scheduling subscriptions ($16-$49/mo) and the bundled Squarespace AI tooling.

The Design Intelligence suite layers AI throughout the platform: the Blueprint AI Builder walks new users through a guided 5-step site build, AI Brand Identity tools generate logo, palette, and typography systems from a brand description, AI text generators produce on-brand copy in any block, and the Beacon AI business assistant answers operator questions inside the dashboard. Squarespace AI is included on every plan, including the free 14-day trial, with no add-on cost.

Beyond the core builder, Squarespace bundles a serious e-commerce stack (unlimited products on every plan, 0% transaction fees on Plus and Advanced, abandoned cart, customer accounts, integrated shipping), the Acuity Scheduling product (originally a separate acquisition, now sold both standalone and bundled), Squarespace Email Campaigns, member areas, courses, and a domains business. Distribution runs through an Impact-managed affiliate program with strong reach in the design and creator-economy review ecosystems.', 'https://www.squarespace.com', 'paid', '[{"plan":"Basic","price":"$16/mo","features":["Unlimited products","Squarespace AI on all plans","SSL and unlimited bandwidth","3% transaction fee on commerce"]},{"plan":"Core","price":"$23/mo","features":["Unlimited products","Custom code blocks","Discounts and gift cards","3% transaction fee"]},{"plan":"Plus","price":"$39/mo","features":["0% transaction fees","Abandoned cart recovery","Customer accounts","Advanced shipping"]},{"plan":"Advanced","price":"$99/mo","features":["0% transaction fees","API access","Subscriptions and limited availability","Advanced commerce analytics"]}]'::jsonb, 'beginner', true, '{"web","mobile","api"}', '{"Award-winning design templates","Blueprint AI Builder (5-step guided build)","AI Brand Identity (logo, palette, typography)","Squarespace AI text generation in all blocks","Beacon AI business assistant","Native commerce with unlimited products","Acuity Scheduling integration (separate plan)","Member areas and paid courses","Email Campaigns built-in","Squarespace Domains and free domain on annual plans","Mobile editor and content apps","Built-in SEO and analytics"}', '{"Stripe","PayPal","Square","Mailchimp","Google Analytics","Acuity Scheduling","Zapier","Meta Pixel","Printful","Instagram"}', true, '{"Designers and creatives building portfolio sites","Service businesses bundling site plus Acuity scheduling","Brand-led small businesses prioritising visual polish","Restaurants, hotels, and hospitality with reservation needs"}', '{"High-volume e-commerce operators (Shopify wins clearly)","Sites needing deep custom backend logic (Webflow / headless fits better)","Hyper-budget users (Wix free tier is more generous)"}', 'The most design-forward mainstream site builder in 2026 — pick Squarespace when brand and typography matter, skip it when you need maximum customisation or Shopify-class commerce.', '{"https://support.squarespace.com/"}', 'Customisation is template-bounded — heavy design changes require Custom CSS or a developer, and the Fluid Engine editor still constrains layout in ways Webflow doesn''t. Acuity Scheduling is sold separately on top of the website plan, which surprises some buyers expecting it to be bundled. Transaction fees of 3% apply on Basic and Core plans for every commerce sale, which can exceed the cost of upgrading to Plus for active sellers. AI text outputs are competent but generic; treat them as a starter draft, not finished copy. Plan migration paths from older Personal / Business plans introduced confusion in the rollout phase.', '{}', '{"reddit_threads":[]}'::jsonb, '{"Launch a designer or photographer portfolio with editorial polish in a weekend.","Run a service business with website plus Acuity scheduling plus Stripe checkout integrated.","Sell a 200-product apparel store on the Plus plan with 0% transaction fees.","Build a paid membership site with members-only content and recurring billing."}', 'Sweet spot: a designer, creator, restaurant, hotel, or brand-led small business where the website is a first impression and visual identity is doing real work for the business. Squarespace''s template quality and Design Intelligence tooling produce sites that look intentional and on-brand without requiring a designer, which is rare in this category. The Acuity bundle (paid separately but tightly integrated) makes it a strong pick for any service business that takes appointments.

Failure modes. First, picking Squarespace for a serious e-commerce operation — once you scale past 200-300 SKUs or need granular shipping rules, Shopify will save more in operational headaches than Squarespace saves in subscription cost. Second, underestimating the Acuity surcharge — modelled together, Squarespace plus Acuity for a service business runs $40-$70/month, not the headline $16-$23. Third, relying too heavily on Squarespace AI for copy on a brand-led site defeats the point of the platform; the design polish only pays off if the words match.

What to pilot. Take the 14-day trial, pick a template close to your brand direction, and run Blueprint AI to seed initial structure. Migrate your real content (about, services, portfolio, products) into the editor and stress-test on mobile. If the design feels close to right within an evening of editing, the platform is well-fitted. If you find yourself fighting the editor to move pixels, Webflow or a developer-built site is probably the better long-term answer.', now()),
('Mixo', 'mixo', 'AI startup landing-page builder that generates a full site from a one-line idea — the indie-hacker favourite for 30-second MVPs.', 'Mixo is an AI website builder positioned squarely at the indie-hacker, no-code, and idea-validation crowd: type a one-line description of your startup idea, and Mixo generates a complete branded landing page in under a minute — hero copy, supporting sections, CTA buttons, AI-generated images, an email-capture form wired to a built-in subscriber list, and a mobile-responsive layout. The pitch since launch has been radical speed: idea to live URL in 30 seconds, no design or copy decisions required, ready to share on Product Hunt or X for feedback before you write a line of code.

The 2026 product extends well beyond single landing pages. Mixo now generates multi-page sites, lets users add pages and edit content with AI-assisted blocks, supports custom domains with free SSL and a free first-year domain on Basic and above, includes built-in subscriber management with GDPR-compliant forms, integrates with social media, ships real-time analytics, and offers conversion-optimised CTA components. Pricing runs free (one page on a yoursite.mixo.io subdomain with branding), Basic at $9/mo, Growth at $19/mo (up to 5 pages with extended AI tools), and Premium at $39/mo for larger sites with deeper customisation.

Mixo''s position in 2026 is the fastest path from idea to validation landing page — a different niche from Wix or Squarespace, which target real ongoing businesses. The in-house affiliate program is a steady performer in the indie-hacker / Twitter-builder ecosystem, where Mixo gets recommended any time someone tweets "what should I use to validate this idea?"', 'https://www.mixo.io', 'freemium', '[{"plan":"Free","price":"$0","features":["1 page on Mixo subdomain","Mixo branding","AI site generation","Subscriber capture"]},{"plan":"Basic","price":"$9/mo","features":["Custom domain","SSL certificate","Free domain first year","No Mixo branding"]},{"plan":"Growth","price":"$19/mo","features":["Up to 5 pages","Extended AI page generation","Advanced subscriber management","More form options"]},{"plan":"Premium","price":"$39/mo","features":["Larger sites","More customisation options","Priority support","All Growth features"]}]'::jsonb, 'beginner', false, '{"web"}', '{"AI site generation from a one-line prompt","AI-generated copy, images, and section structure","Built-in subscriber and email-capture forms","GDPR-compliant forms with anti-spam","Custom domain support with free SSL","Real-time site analytics","Mobile-responsive output by default","Conversion-optimised CTAs","Social media integration","SEO meta editing","Multi-page site support (Growth+)","Free first-year domain (Basic+)"}', '{"Mailchimp","Stripe","Google Analytics","Zapier","Meta Pixel","Custom domains via DNS"}', true, '{"Indie hackers validating an idea before building anything","Solo founders launching a waitlist or coming-soon page","Side-project teams shipping a quick landing page in an evening","Marketers spinning up campaign-specific microsites"}', '{"Real ongoing businesses needing booking, e-commerce, or blog (Wix wins)","Brand-led portfolio sites with high design demands (Squarespace fits better)","Teams needing CMS-grade content management"}', 'The fastest idea-to-landing-page tool in 2026 — pick Mixo when you need a waitlist or validation page in 30 seconds, skip it when you need a real ongoing business website.', '{"https://help.mixo.io/"}', 'Output is intentionally generic — every Mixo site starts with structurally similar AI-generated copy and images, and many indie-hacker sites end up looking like each other unless you swap in real assets. The AI image generator produces serviceable but not striking visuals; serious launches will need to replace them. Customisation depth is shallow vs Wix or Squarespace — heavy design changes are not the platform''s purpose. The free tier carries Mixo branding and a subdomain, which is fine for testing but not for serious launches. Beyond simple landing or coming-soon pages, the product is not the right fit — Mixo is a validation tool, not a long-term home.', '{}', '{"reddit_threads":[]}'::jsonb, '{"Launch a coming-soon page with email capture for an unbuilt SaaS in 30 seconds.","Validate a startup idea by sharing a Mixo URL on Product Hunt and X to gauge interest.","Spin up 10 different microsite variants to A/B-test positioning before building.","Capture a waitlist before writing a single line of code for an MVP."}', 'Sweet spot: an indie hacker, solo founder, or product manager validating an idea who needs a credible-looking landing page within minutes — not hours, not days. Mixo''s value is collapsing the cold-start problem for idea validation: instead of fighting Webflow or paying a designer just to test whether anyone wants the thing, you ship a page, run a $50 ad campaign or share it on social, and measure email signups. That feedback loop is what Mixo optimises for.

Failure modes. First, treating Mixo as a long-term website — the platform is built for fast launches, not ongoing content management, and you''ll outgrow it the moment your idea works. Plan to migrate to Webflow, Wix, or a custom build once validated. Second, leaning on the AI-generated copy and images for a real launch — they''re placeholders, not finished assets, and savvy visitors notice. Replace at least the hero and core CTA with real content before traffic hits. Third, expecting deep customisation; if you find yourself fighting the editor, you''re using the wrong tool.

What to pilot. Type your idea into the free generator, get a page live, and run a $30-$100 paid traffic test (Reddit ads, X ads, or a niche newsletter sponsorship) over 7 days. Measure cost-per-email-signup. If the unit economics make sense and signups feel real, you have validation — graduate to a real builder. If signups are flat, the failure is the offer, not the page, and Mixo just saved you a month of build time.', now()),
('HeadshotPro', 'headshotpro', 'AI professional headshot generator that turns selfies into LinkedIn-ready studio photos for individuals and teams.', 'HeadshotPro is one of the longest-running and most-used AI headshot products in the market — a tool that takes 10-15 casual selfies, trains a personal model on the user''s face, and generates 40-240 professional studio-quality headshots across 300+ backdrops and 300+ outfit styles. The product replaces the traditional photographer-and-studio session for the LinkedIn / corporate-website / team-photo use case, where the goal is "look professional and consistent" rather than artistic portraiture.

The 2026 product offers three individual tiers — Small Shoot ($29 for 40 headshots), Normal Shoot ($39 for 120 headshots), and Premium Shoot ($49 for 240 headshots) — and a team plan at $39 per person with a 20% discount for groups of 5+. Turnaround runs from 1 hour on premium tiers to 2-3 hours on standard tiers. The company reports 18M+ headshots generated across 197K+ customers and a 4.8 Trustpilot score. Privacy policy auto-deletes input selfies after 7 days and generated headshots after 30 days, and full commercial rights to outputs are included.

HeadshotPro''s position in 2026 is the established team-headshots and LinkedIn-headshots leader. BetterPic and Aragon compete on quality, but HeadshotPro''s team workflow (a single admin can onboard 50 employees and order matching headshots in one batch) is what wins distributed-team and remote-company customers. The in-house affiliate program is well-managed and converts steadily on B2B channels.', 'https://www.headshotpro.com', 'paid', '[{"plan":"Small Shoot","price":"$29 one-time","features":["40 headshots","300+ backdrops","300+ outfits","2-3 hour turnaround"]},{"plan":"Normal Shoot","price":"$39 one-time","features":["120 headshots","Wider style variety","Faster turnaround","Most popular individual tier"]},{"plan":"Premium Shoot","price":"$49 one-time","features":["240 headshots","Fastest 1-hour turnaround","Maximum style variety","Premium quality"]},{"plan":"Team","price":"$39 per person","features":["Group admin workflow","20% discount for 5+ members","Consistent backdrops across team","Bulk onboarding"]}]'::jsonb, 'beginner', false, '{"web"}', '{"Personal AI model trained from 10-15 selfies","300+ studio backdrops","300+ outfit styles","40-240 generated headshots per shoot","1-3 hour turnaround","Team workflow with admin batch management","Full commercial rights and ownership","Auto-delete of input photos after 7 days","High-resolution exports","Background colour and style variety","Consistent team-photo styling","No subscription — pay per shoot"}', '{"Direct download","Email delivery","Team admin dashboard","Stripe payment"}', true, '{"Remote teams needing consistent LinkedIn-ready headshots","Job seekers refreshing their LinkedIn for a search","Founders needing press-kit and About-page photos","Sales reps standardising profile photos across LinkedIn and CRM"}', '{"Artistic portrait photography use cases","High-stakes branding shoots where authenticity matters","Subjects with unusual lighting or styling needs"}', 'The most-used AI headshot tool in 2026 — pick HeadshotPro for fast LinkedIn and team headshots, skip it when you need genuine photographic portraiture.', '{"https://help.headshotpro.com/"}', 'Output quality varies meaningfully by input selfie quality — bad lighting or poor angles in source photos produce visible artefacts (asymmetric features, weird ear placement, hand distortions). The AI sometimes alters subtle facial features in ways subjects find off-putting; expect to discard 30-50% of generated images. Style variety, while wide, leans corporate-conservative — creative or artistic looks are limited. There''s no subscription, which is positive for one-time use but means returning customers pay full price for each new shoot. Backgrounds occasionally show telltale AI artefacts like ambiguous architecture or impossible lighting.', '{}', '{"reddit_threads":[]}'::jsonb, '{"Refresh a LinkedIn profile photo in under 2 hours without a photographer.","Onboard a 30-person remote team with consistent headshots for the company About page.","Generate a press-kit photo set across multiple backgrounds for a founder.","Standardise sales-rep profile photos across CRM, LinkedIn, and email signatures."}', 'Sweet spot: a remote-first team or distributed company that needs consistent professional headshots for the entire workforce without flying everyone to a studio. HeadshotPro''s team workflow and 20%+ bulk discount make 30-person rollouts trivial — admin uploads selfies, picks consistent backdrops, batch-orders, and gets matching photos within a day. For individuals, the LinkedIn-refresh use case is the obvious win at $29-$49 versus $200-$500 for a real photographer.

Failure modes. First, garbage-in produces garbage-out — selfies must be well-lit, varied in angle, and from the last 6 months. Customers who upload 10-year-old photos get unrecognisable outputs. Second, the AI sometimes "improves" facial features in ways that subjects find inauthentic; review outputs honestly before uploading to LinkedIn — a fake-looking photo damages credibility more than no photo. Third, expect to use only 5-10% of generated images; ordering the largest shoot just to have variety is rational. Fourth, hands are still a known weakness — most polished outputs are head-and-shoulder crops only.

What to pilot. Run one Small Shoot ($29) for yourself before committing a team. Upload a clean selfie set (10-15 photos, varied angles, recent, well-lit), pick 3-4 backdrops, and review outputs critically. If you''d use 2-3 of the 40 outputs on LinkedIn, the team-scale rollout will produce equivalent hit rates. If you can''t find a single usable image, the bottleneck is either your input photos or your face''s fit with current AI models — try BetterPic or Aragon before scaling.', now()),
('PhotoAI', 'photoai', 'Pieter Levels'' AI photo, portrait, fashion, fitness, and influencer image generator from a few selfies.', 'PhotoAI is the indie-built generative photo platform from Pieter Levels (the Dutch indie entrepreneur behind Nomads.com, Remote OK, and Interior AI) that famously grew from $0 to $132K+ MRR in under 18 months and is now the highest-grossing single-developer AI product in the consumer image-generation category. The pitch is simple: upload a small set of selfies, train a personal AI model of your face, then generate unlimited photorealistic photos and short videos of yourself in any setting, outfit, pose, or scenario — portrait, fashion, fitness, influencer-style content, professional headshots, travel shots, lifestyle imagery.

The 2026 product line covers five subscription tiers — Starter ($19/mo), Pro ($49/mo, 1,000 credits and up to 5 AI characters), Premium ($99/mo, 5,000-image limit and up to 25 characters with parallel generation), and Business ($199/mo, 25,000 images and up to 100 characters) — with annual billing roughly 50% cheaper than monthly. The platform supports image and short-video generation, 3D representations of any photo in one click, and integrations with current frontier image models including Google''s Nano Banana Pro under PhotoAI''s identity-preservation pipeline. Levels has been transparent on Twitter / X about every architectural and pricing decision, which has built unusual community trust.

PhotoAI''s position in 2026 is the dominant consumer / creator photo-generation tool — broader than HeadshotPro''s narrow professional-headshot focus, more polished than open-source Replicate workflows, more flexible than Midjourney for personal-character generation. The in-house affiliate program is widely promoted in the AI-tools and creator-economy review ecosystem.', 'https://photoai.com', 'paid', '[{"plan":"Starter","price":"$19/mo","features":["Entry tier","Limited credits","1 AI character","Standard generation queue"]},{"plan":"Pro","price":"$49/mo","features":["1,000 4K images per month","Up to 5 AI characters","Faster generation","Image and video generation"]},{"plan":"Premium","price":"$99/mo","features":["5,000 images per month","Up to 25 AI characters","8 photos in parallel","Priority queue"]},{"plan":"Business","price":"$199/mo","features":["25,000 images per month","Up to 100 AI characters","Highest priority","Annual save 50%+ vs monthly"]}]'::jsonb, 'beginner', true, '{"web","api"}', '{"Personal AI character training from selfies","Photorealistic image generation in any scene or style","Short AI video generation","3D photo conversion (one-click)","Multiple AI characters per account","Parallel generation (Premium+)","Fashion, fitness, portrait, and influencer presets","Integration with frontier models (Nano Banana Pro)","High-resolution 4K output","Annual plans 50%+ cheaper","API access on higher tiers","Negative-prompt and style controls"}', '{"Stripe","Direct download","API webhook delivery","Image upload from URL"}', true, '{"Creators producing influencer-style content without shoots","Founders generating press, lifestyle, and travel imagery","Fashion and fitness creators producing brand-aligned visuals","Solo professionals replacing photographer fees with AI generation"}', '{"Brand campaigns requiring genuine photography (consumers detect AI)","Use cases requiring guaranteed authenticity (journalism, ID photos)","Highly regulated visual content (medical, legal, evidentiary)"}', 'The most successful indie-built AI photo platform in 2026 — pick PhotoAI for personal-creator imagery at scale, skip it when authenticity or campaign-grade photography is required.', '{"https://photoai.com/faq"}', 'Generated images vary in identity preservation — close family members occasionally don''t recognise the subject in less-flattering generations, so review honestly before posting. Hands, ears, and complex backgrounds remain failure points across all current image models, including PhotoAI''s pipeline. Per-credit economics on lower tiers run out fast for active creators — most serious users land on Pro or Premium. Some image-model integrations (Nano Banana Pro etc.) inherit upstream policy restrictions that block certain prompts. Indie ownership means support is leaner than a venture-funded competitor — Levels and a small team handle issues directly, which is fast for some users and frustrating for those expecting enterprise SLAs.', '{}', '{"reddit_threads":[]}'::jsonb, '{"Generate weekly Instagram lifestyle and travel content without taking the trip.","Produce a fashion lookbook for a personal brand without booking a photographer.","Create a fitness-progress photo series in consistent lighting and outfits.","Generate a year of varied LinkedIn and About-page photos from one selfie set."}', 'Sweet spot: a creator, solo founder, or personal brand who needs a constant stream of on-brand photos of themselves and would otherwise pay a photographer monthly or simply post less because shoots are friction. PhotoAI at $49-$99/month replaces a $1K-$3K/month photographer retainer for the right user — and unlocks photo concepts (snowy mountain, Tokyo street, fitness gym at sunset) that are logistically impossible without travel and crew.

Failure modes. First, treating PhotoAI as a brand-campaign replacement — agencies and audiences increasingly detect AI photography, and reputational damage from a fake "real" campaign exceeds the cost savings. Reserve PhotoAI for personal-content workflows, not paid brand work. Second, identity drift — at higher creativity settings the model starts looking like someone adjacent to you rather than you. Train carefully, review honestly, and discard generations that don''t look like the real person. Third, ethical and disclosure norms are evolving fast — consumer audiences in 2026 expect disclosure on AI-generated personal imagery in many contexts. Build disclosure into your posting workflow.

What to pilot. Subscribe to Pro for one month, train one AI character on a clean selfie set (15-20 varied recent photos, good lighting), and generate 200 images across 5-6 prompts you''d realistically use. Honestly assess identity preservation — ask three close people if the photos look like you. If yes, the unit economics replace traditional photography immediately. If identity drift is bad, retrain with a tighter selfie set or accept that current AI doesn''t fit your face well yet (some faces train better than others, no platform fully solves this).', now()),
('Try It On AI', 'tryitonai', 'AI headshot generator that turns a single selfie into professional studio-quality portraits in minutes.', 'Try It On AI is an AI headshot and portrait studio that takes one or more selfies and produces a batch of professional-grade headshots without a photographer, studio, or makeup artist. The product''s core promise is convenience plus fidelity: upload a phone selfie, pick the wardrobe / background / styling presets you want, and within a few minutes you have 20–100+ usable headshots in resolutions suitable for LinkedIn, corporate websites, legal directories, real-estate listings, dating profiles, and press kits. The platform claims 3M+ users and is widely cited (WSJ, Forbes) as one of the leading consumer AI-headshot tools.

Beyond solo creators, Try It On AI runs a Teams product aimed at law firms, consulting partners, agencies, and remote-first companies that need consistent, on-brand headshots across a distributed workforce — a use case where flying everyone to a studio is impractical. The Teams flow handles bulk uploads, brand-consistent backgrounds and wardrobe palettes, and per-employee delivery, plus optional human edits ($10/image) for cases where the AI output needs touch-ups (logo on a t-shirt, specific background composition, retouching).

Compared to alternatives (Aragon, Secta Labs, Headshot Pro), Try It On AI sits at the consumer / SMB end of the market with strong volume pricing for teams and a simple per-pack purchase model rather than a heavy subscription. The in-house affiliate program is a fit for career, professional-development, legal, and remote-work content audiences.', 'https://tryitonai.com', 'paid', '[{"plan":"Express","price":"$35 one-time","features":["20 AI headshots","Standard styles","2-minute generation","Standard resolution"]},{"plan":"Premium","price":"$45 one-time","features":["40+ headshots","All style presets","Higher resolution","Priority queue"]},{"plan":"Creative Studio","price":"$19/mo","features":["Ongoing generations","All styles and backgrounds","Cancel anytime","Lower per-image cost"]},{"plan":"Teams","price":"From $21/person","features":["Bulk uploads","Brand-consistent styling","Volume discounts","Centralised delivery"]}]'::jsonb, 'beginner', false, '{"web"}', '{"AI headshot generation from a single selfie","Multiple wardrobe and background presets","Professional studio-style lighting simulation","Bulk team upload and processing","Brand-consistent styling for company teams","Optional human edits ($10/image)","Lawyer / corporate / startup vertical packs","High-resolution output for LinkedIn and press","Style mixing across one upload set","Privacy-conscious selfie deletion after generation"}', '{"LinkedIn","Stripe","Email delivery","Slack (team rollout)","Zapier"}', true, '{"Job seekers refreshing a LinkedIn profile photo on a budget","Remote teams needing consistent on-brand headshots without a studio","Lawyers and consultants updating firm directory photos","Founders preparing press-kit and About-page portraits"}', '{"Editorial / fashion photography needing real-world fidelity","Anyone uncomfortable with AI-generated likenesses on professional profiles","High-stakes campaigns where uncanny-valley artefacts are unacceptable"}', 'The most accessible consumer AI-headshot tool in 2026 — pick it for fast, cheap, presentable headshots; skip it when authenticity matters more than convenience.', '{"https://www.tryitonai.com/faqs"}', 'Output quality varies meaningfully by input selfie — poor lighting, off-angle shots, or cluttered backgrounds in the source produce visible artefacts (warped ears, asymmetric glasses, inconsistent jawlines) in the AI output. Pack-based pricing means you commit before seeing results, and remediation requires the $10/image human-edit add-on or a fresh pack purchase. Some industries (legal, finance, executive search) still expect human-photographed headshots; AI-generated likenesses can read as inauthentic to senior recruiters or partners. No API or programmatic access — strictly a self-serve web app.', '{}', '{"reddit_threads":[]}'::jsonb, '{"Generate 20 LinkedIn headshots from one weekend selfie session for under $40.","Roll out consistent on-brand team headshots across a 50-person remote company.","Update a law-firm directory with uniform-style portraits without coordinating a studio shoot.","Produce founder press-kit photos for a launch announcement on a startup budget."}', 'Sweet spot: a job seeker, freelancer, or remote team that needs presentable professional headshots fast and cheap, and where the alternative is either no headshot or a $300+ studio session that won''t happen. Try It On AI hits a real price-quality point for the LinkedIn / company-bio use case where 95% of viewers will never zoom in close enough to spot AI artefacts.

Failure modes. First, expect 30–50% of generated images to be unusable per pack — the platform produces volume on purpose and the keepers come from filtering. Don''t buy the smallest pack hoping for perfection. Second, AI-generated headshots are increasingly recognisable as such, and some professional contexts (executive search, legal partner bios, finance) penalise rather than reward them — know your audience before using AI output. Third, the source selfie matters more than any prompt or style choice; spend 10 minutes shooting good source selfies in even lighting before uploading.

What to pilot. Buy the cheapest Express pack ($35) with one set of well-shot selfies. Filter to your top 3–5 keepers and put them through a real-world test — A/B them against your current LinkedIn photo for a week and check profile-view changes, or get feedback from 5 colleagues blind. If the AI headshot reads as professional and current, scale to the larger pack or Teams plan for the rest of your org. If it reads as off, the bottleneck is the medium, not the tool.', now()),
('Manatal', 'manatal', 'AI-powered ATS and recruitment CRM built for SMB hiring teams and agencies, with the lowest per-seat pricing in the category.', 'Manatal is a Bangkok-headquartered applicant tracking system and recruitment CRM aimed at SMB in-house hiring teams and recruitment agencies. The product''s positioning has been consistent since launch: deliver 80% of the functionality of enterprise ATS platforms (Greenhouse, Lever, SmartRecruiters) at roughly 10% of the per-seat cost, while doubling down on AI-driven candidate matching and CRM-style relationship tracking that agencies actually need. Manatal serves 10,000+ companies across 135 countries.

The 2024–2026 product layers AI throughout the funnel: AI Recommendations score and rank candidates against any open job, AI Candidate Enrichment scrapes public sources (LinkedIn, GitHub, personal sites) to fill out thin profiles automatically, and the optional AI Interviewer add-on conducts 24/7 multilingual video screening and scores responses against a rubric. The agency-facing CRM side is where Manatal differentiates from in-house-focused tools — recruiters can pitch placed candidates to multiple clients, track placement fees, and run client-portal collaboration without a separate Bullhorn-style CRM bill.

Manatal''s position in 2026 is the value-priced ATS for SMBs and agencies. Workable / Greenhouse own the mid-market and up; Manatal owns the long tail of 1–50 employee companies and small agencies that need a real ATS but can''t justify $300+/month per seat. The in-house affiliate program is well-established in the recruitment-tooling content space.', 'https://www.manatal.com', 'paid', '[{"plan":"Professional","price":"$15/user/mo","features":["15 jobs","Core ATS","AI recommendations","Career site","Email integration"]},{"plan":"Enterprise","price":"$35/user/mo","features":["Unlimited jobs","Recruitment CRM","Client portal","Mass emails","Custom reports"]},{"plan":"Enterprise Plus","price":"$55/user/mo","features":["API access","Custom roles and permissions","SSO","Advanced security","Priority support"]},{"plan":"Custom","price":"Custom","features":["All Enterprise Plus features","Custom integrations","Dedicated support","Onboarding services"]}]'::jsonb, 'beginner', true, '{"web","mobile","api"}', '{"AI candidate recommendations and ranking","AI candidate enrichment from public sources","Recruitment CRM for agencies","Drag-and-drop kanban pipeline","Career site builder","Job board posting (2,500+ boards)","Client portal for agency-client collaboration","Mass email and template library","Custom reports and dashboards","AI Interviewer add-on (multilingual video screening)","REST API (Enterprise Plus and above)","Mobile apps (iOS and Android)"}', '{"LinkedIn","Indeed","Gmail","Outlook","Microsoft 365","Slack","Zapier","Make","Calendly","DocuSign"}', true, '{"SMB hiring teams running 5–50 open roles","Recruitment agencies placing candidates across multiple clients","Cost-conscious startups hiring their first dozen employees","Companies in emerging markets where enterprise ATS pricing is unaffordable"}', '{"Enterprise hiring orgs needing deep workflow customisation (Greenhouse / SmartRecruiters fit)","Companies needing tight HRIS integration with Workday / SuccessFactors","High-volume hourly hiring (specialist tools like Fountain fit better)"}', 'The best per-dollar ATS in 2026 for SMBs and agencies — pick it when budget rules and you don''t need enterprise workflow depth.', '{"https://help.manatal.com/"}', 'API access is locked to Enterprise Plus ($55/user/month), which prevents Professional-tier customers from integrating with HRIS or custom internal tools. The Professional plan caps at 15 jobs, which growing teams hit fast and forces a tier upgrade. AI Interviewer is a paid add-on, not bundled. Reporting is solid for an SMB tool but lacks the analyst-grade depth of Greenhouse or Workable Premier. UI is functional but feels less polished than Lever or Greenhouse — recruiters coming from those tools notice the difference in the first week.', '{}', '{"reddit_threads":[]}'::jsonb, '{"Run an SMB ATS with AI candidate ranking across 30 open roles for under $500/month.","Manage a 10-recruiter agency placing candidates across 50 client accounts.","Automatically enrich candidate profiles from LinkedIn and GitHub without manual scraping.","Screen high-volume applicants with the AI Interviewer add-on before human interviews."}', 'Sweet spot: a 5–100 person company with 5–30 open roles, or a 2–20 recruiter agency that needs both ATS and CRM under one bill. Manatal''s economics are genuinely hard to beat at the SMB band — a 10-recruiter agency on Enterprise pays $350/month, while the equivalent Bullhorn + Greenhouse stack runs 5–10x that. The AI candidate-ranking quality is good enough for the SMB volumes the platform serves; it isn''t Greenhouse-grade but it doesn''t need to be at the price point.

Failure modes. First, hitting the 15-job ceiling on Professional triggers a forced jump to Enterprise that more than doubles the bill — model the upgrade cost at signup, not retroactively. Second, the AI Interviewer add-on is impressive in demos but candidate-experience reviews are mixed; treat it as a screening filter, not a replacement for human first-rounds. Third, integrations with North American HRIS (Workday, BambooHR, SuccessFactors) are thinner than what Workable / Greenhouse offer — verify your HRIS is supported before committing.

What to pilot. Run the 14-day trial with one real open role: post the job, source 30 candidates, run them through the AI ranking, and have your recruiter compare AI rankings to their own gut order. If the rankings correlate (top 5 matches in both lists overlap meaningfully), the AI is doing real work and the price-per-seat justifies the migration. If rankings diverge significantly, treat the AI as a filter aid, not a decision tool.', now()),
('Workable', 'workable', 'AI-powered recruitment platform combining ATS, sourcing, and screening for SMB and mid-market hiring teams.', 'Workable is one of the longest-running and most widely-deployed SMB / mid-market ATS platforms — Greek-founded in 2012, used by 30,000+ companies globally. The product covers the full hiring funnel: branded careers pages, multi-board job posting (200+ free and premium boards in one click), candidate sourcing across a 400M+ profile database, an applicant pipeline with kanban and structured interview kits, automated reference checks, offer letters with e-signature, and a built-in HRIS for new-hire onboarding once a candidate is hired.

The 2024–2026 AI layer is central to Workable''s positioning: AI Recruiter scans the 400M+ profile database against any job description and surfaces ranked matches based on career trajectory and skills fit (not just keyword matches), AI Screening Assistant ranks inbound applicants with explainable scoring, AI-generated job descriptions and screening questions, and AI candidate summaries that compress long resumes into one-paragraph briefings for hiring managers. The SEEK partnership feeds candidate-progression data back into the matching engine to improve relevance over time.

Workable''s position in 2026 is the default ATS for 20–500 employee companies that have outgrown Manatal / BambooHR Hire but don''t need Greenhouse / Lever''s enterprise depth. The headcount-based pricing (rather than per-recruiter-seat) makes it predictable for growing companies but creates a "cliff effect" at headcount tier boundaries. The in-house partner program is well-established in the recruitment-tooling content space.', 'https://www.workable.com', 'paid', '[{"plan":"Starter","price":"$149/mo (1–20 employees)","features":["2 active jobs","Core ATS","Branded careers page","Email integration"]},{"plan":"Standard","price":"$299/mo (1–20 employees)","features":["Unlimited jobs","AI Recruiter sourcing","Advanced reporting","Interview kits","Texting"]},{"plan":"Premier","price":"$599/mo (1–20 employees)","features":["Advanced analytics","SSO","Custom roles","Priority support","Dedicated CSM"]},{"plan":"Pay-As-You-Go","price":"$99/job/mo","features":["Single active job","No annual commitment","Full ATS features","Ideal for sporadic hiring"]}]'::jsonb, 'beginner', true, '{"web","mobile","api"}', '{"AI Recruiter sourcing across 400M+ profiles","AI Screening Assistant with explainable ranking","AI-generated job descriptions and screening questions","AI candidate summaries from full resumes","Multi-board job posting (200+ boards)","Branded careers pages","Structured interview kits and scorecards","Texting and video interviews","E-signature offer letters","Automated reference checks","Built-in HRIS for new-hire onboarding","Reporting and EEO/OFCCP compliance"}', '{"LinkedIn","Indeed","Glassdoor","Slack","Microsoft Teams","Google Calendar","BambooHR","Okta","DocuSign","Zapier"}', true, '{"SMB and mid-market companies with 20–500 employees","HR teams that need AI sourcing without enterprise complexity","Companies hiring across 5–50 open roles per quarter","Hiring teams replacing email + spreadsheet with a real ATS"}', '{"Companies under 5 employees with one annual hire (use pay-per-job or free options)","Enterprise teams needing deep workflow customisation (Greenhouse / Lever)","Pure agencies / staffing firms (Bullhorn / Manatal fit better)"}', 'A reliable, broadly-deployed SMB / mid-market ATS with credible AI sourcing — pick it for predictable hiring volume, model the headcount cliff effect carefully.', '{"https://help.workable.com/"}', 'Headcount-based pricing creates surprising cliffs — adding one employee can push a company from the 1–20 tier to the 21–50 tier and increase the bill by 60–70% overnight. AI Recruiter sourcing is locked to Standard and above. Some integrations (HRIS, payroll) feel surface-level vs deeper Greenhouse equivalents. Mobile app is functional but lags the web product. Customer support quality has fluctuated since the company''s 2023 reorganisation; response times on Starter are slower than Manatal at a higher price point.', '{}', '{"reddit_threads":[]}'::jsonb, '{"Run a 50-person company''s entire hiring funnel — from job posting to offer signature.","Use AI Recruiter to surface 50 ranked passive candidates for a hard-to-fill engineering role.","Auto-screen 500 inbound applicants down to a top-20 shortlist with explainable ranking.","Replace a spreadsheet + email hiring process with a structured ATS without enterprise lift."}', 'Sweet spot: a 20–500 person company with 5–30 open roles per quarter where hiring is important but not the entire business. Workable''s breadth (sourcing + ATS + onboarding under one bill) is the right shape for that band, and the AI sourcing genuinely lifts pipeline quality when the underlying job description is well-written. The 400M-profile database is a real asset — most SMB ATS tools don''t have a sourcing layer at all.

Failure modes. First, the headcount cliff effect catches growing companies off guard — a 20-person company that hires its 21st employee jumps to a higher pricing tier and bill, so model the next 12 months of headcount growth before signing. Second, AI Recruiter quality depends entirely on the job description; vague or outdated JDs produce noisy candidate matches. Invest in JD craft before blaming the AI. Third, the platform''s breadth means individual modules (HRIS, onboarding) are competent rather than best-in-class — companies serious about HRIS will outgrow Workable''s built-in onboarding and need BambooHR / HiBob alongside.

What to pilot. Run the 15-day trial with two real open roles: one easy (high-volume inbound) and one hard (passive-sourcing required). On the easy role, measure how well AI Screening Assistant ranks inbound applicants vs your recruiter''s manual sort. On the hard role, evaluate AI Recruiter''s sourced candidates for actual fit and response rate. If both AI surfaces produce 5+ usable candidates, the pricing is justified. If results are weak, the bottleneck is JD craft or ICP definition.', now()),
('Recruitee', 'recruitee', 'Collaborative ATS with AI job description writer and screening assistant, built for mid-market hiring teams.', 'Recruitee is an Amsterdam-founded ATS (2015, acquired by Tellent in 2022 alongside Javelo and KiwiHR) that has built its reputation on collaborative hiring — the idea that hiring should involve the entire team, not just the recruiter. The product is heavy on shared pipelines, hiring-manager scorecards, structured interview kits, and a customisable kanban that gives every stakeholder visibility into where each candidate sits. The 2024–2026 product is now the flagship ATS in Tellent''s broader HR suite, alongside performance management (Javelo) and HRIS (KiwiHR), with cross-product data sharing for companies that buy more than one Tellent module.

The AI layer in 2026 is targeted and useful rather than gimmicky: an AI job-description writer that drafts complete JDs from a role title and seniority, AI-drafted candidate communication emails, AI feedback summarisation that compresses scattered hiring-manager comments into a single decision-ready brief, and the AI Screening Assistant (100 credits/month standard, more on higher tiers) that ranks inbound applicants with explainable scoring while keeping a human in the loop on every decision.

Recruitee''s position in 2026 is the collaborative-hiring ATS for mid-market European companies and US SMBs that take cross-team hiring seriously. Workable owns the broader SMB market on integrations and AI sourcing breadth; Recruitee owns the pocket where careers-site customisation, multi-language support, and team-collaboration UX matter more. The in-house affiliate / partner program runs through Tellent''s broader partner ecosystem.', 'https://recruitee.com', 'paid', '[{"plan":"Start","price":"€149/mo","features":["Up to 10 jobs","Core ATS","Career site","Email integration","Standard automations"]},{"plan":"Grow","price":"$345/mo","features":["Unlimited jobs and users","Career site builder","Analytics","AI Screening Assistant (100 credits)","Standard automations"]},{"plan":"Optimize","price":"Custom","features":["Multi-language career sites","Advanced automations","Custom roles","SSO","Priority support"]},{"plan":"Lead / Enterprise","price":"From $1,200/mo","features":["Multi-page career sites","Bespoke integrations","Onboarding and implementation","Dedicated CSM"]}]'::jsonb, 'beginner', true, '{"web","mobile","api"}', '{"AI job-description writer","AI Screening Assistant with explainable ranking","AI feedback summarisation across hiring panel","Collaborative kanban pipeline","Structured interview kits and scorecards","Multi-language career site builder","Multi-page career sites (Lead tier)","Job board posting and syndication","Email and calendar integrations","Reporting and analytics","REST API and webhooks","Mobile apps (iOS and Android)"}', '{"LinkedIn","Indeed","Slack","Microsoft Teams","Google Calendar","Outlook","BambooHR","Okta","Zapier","DocuSign"}', true, '{"Mid-market hiring teams that run cross-functional interview panels","European companies needing multi-language careers sites","Companies already using Tellent''s performance / HRIS modules","HR teams replacing siloed email-based hiring with collaborative workflows"}', '{"Solo founders or 1–5 person companies (cheaper tools fit)","Pure agencies / staffing firms (Bullhorn / Manatal fit better)","Companies needing 400M+ candidate-database sourcing (Workable wins)"}', 'A strong collaborative-hiring ATS with thoughtful AI features — pick Recruitee when team involvement and multi-language careers sites matter, pick Workable when AI sourcing breadth matters more.', '{"https://support.recruitee.com/"}', 'Pricing has risen meaningfully since the Tellent acquisition — the Grow tier at $345/mo is no longer the bargain it was in 2022, and Lead/Enterprise tiers start at $1,200/mo before customisation. AI Screening Assistant credits (100/month on Grow) deplete fast for high-volume roles; additional credits cost extra. No native 400M-profile sourcing database — Recruitee assumes you bring the candidates via job boards and referrals. Some North American integrations (Workday, ADP, Gusto) feel less mature than European-market equivalents. The Tellent rebrand caused some customer confusion in 2023–2024.', '{}', '{"reddit_threads":[]}'::jsonb, '{"Run a 5-person interview panel through structured scorecards and AI-summarised feedback.","Build a multi-language careers site for a European company hiring across 8 countries.","Auto-rank 200 inbound applicants for a marketing role with explainable AI scoring.","Replace email-based hiring chaos with a shared kanban that hiring managers actually use."}', 'Sweet spot: a 50–500 person mid-market company (especially European) where hiring is genuinely cross-functional and the careers site is a meaningful brand surface. Recruitee''s collaboration UX is real — hiring managers actually log in and leave structured feedback rather than ignoring the ATS, which is the rare outcome in this category. The multi-language careers site builder is a quiet differentiator that most US-focused ATS tools simply don''t handle well.

Failure modes. First, post-acquisition pricing has crept up and the Lead / Enterprise tiers now feel premium-priced rather than mid-market. Re-quote the platform if you''re looking at multi-year contracts. Second, the 100-credit/month AI Screening cap on Grow runs out in 2–3 weeks for high-volume hiring; budget for the upgrade or limit AI screening to highest-priority roles. Third, the absence of a 400M-profile sourcing database means Recruitee is an inbound / referral / paid-board tool, not a passive-sourcing tool — pair it with LinkedIn Recruiter if you need outbound.

What to pilot. Run the 18-day trial with one real cross-functional hire — ideally a role with 4+ interview-panel stakeholders. Measure how many panel members actually log in and leave structured feedback in Recruitee versus the percentage who would have replied to a "what did you think?" email. If panel-completion rates lift to 80%+ from a typical 40–50%, the collaboration UX is doing real work and the price-per-month is justified. If panel members ignore Recruitee like they ignore every other tool, the bottleneck is process discipline, not software.', now()),
('Envato Elements', 'envato', 'Subscription stock library with unlimited downloads of templates, video, audio, photos, fonts, and graphics — plus AI generation tools.', 'Envato Elements is the flagship subscription product of the Envato Group — a 27 million+ asset stock library covering video footage, motion templates, audio tracks and sound effects, stock photos, fonts, graphic templates, presentation decks, web templates, 3D assets, and code components, all under a single all-you-can-download subscription. Originally launched in 2016 as a flat-rate alternative to Envato Market''s per-item licensing, Elements has grown into one of the largest subscription stock platforms globally and the default creative-library subscription for freelancers, agencies, and content creators outside the Adobe Stock ecosystem.

The February 2026 pricing restructure introduced three tiers — Core, Plus, and Ultimate — with the legacy "unlimited everything" model replaced by tiered AI generation limits. Core ($16.50/month annual) covers unlimited traditional asset downloads with 10 AI generations/month; Plus adds 100 AI generations and Ultimate moves to unlimited AI plus higher-tier creative tools. The shift acknowledges that AI image / video generation is the new high-cost item; legacy users were grandfathered for a transition period.

Envato Elements'' position in 2026 is the broadest single-subscription creative library outside Adobe Stock. Storyblocks competes on video specifically, Artlist owns audio, Freepik owns illustrations and AI imagery — Elements is the generalist that beats specialists on breadth at any single price point. Distribution runs through the Impact affiliate network with strong creator-economy partnerships, and the program is one of the most widely-promoted in design / video tutorial content.', 'https://elements.envato.com', 'paid', '[{"plan":"Core","price":"$16.50/mo annual","features":["Unlimited downloads of 27M+ assets","10 AI generations/mo","Standard commercial licence","Templates, video, audio, photos, fonts"]},{"plan":"Plus","price":"$39/mo annual","features":["Everything in Core","100 AI generations/mo","Premium AI tools","Advanced commercial licence"]},{"plan":"Ultimate","price":"$109/mo annual","features":["Unlimited AI generations","All premium tools","Top-tier creative AI access","Priority support"]},{"plan":"Teams","price":"$33–35/user/mo annual","features":["Centralised billing","Team licence coverage","Shared collections","Admin dashboard"]}]'::jsonb, 'beginner', false, '{"web"}', '{"Unlimited downloads of 27M+ stock assets","Stock video footage and motion graphics","Music tracks and sound effects","Stock photos and illustrations","Fonts and typography","Web and presentation templates","After Effects, Premiere Pro, Final Cut templates","WordPress and Shopify themes","3D assets and graphics","AI image and video generation (tiered limits)","Standard and advanced commercial licensing","Team plans with centralised billing"}', '{"Adobe Photoshop","Adobe Premiere Pro","Adobe After Effects","Final Cut Pro","WordPress","Shopify","Figma","Canva","Slack (Teams plan)"}', true, '{"Freelance designers and video editors needing broad asset coverage","Marketing teams producing high-volume social and web content","Agencies billing client projects with stock-asset markups","Content creators needing music, video, and graphics under one bill"}', '{"Editorial publishers needing rights-managed news photography (Getty / Reuters fit)","Enterprise brands needing custom-shot exclusive content","Teams that already pay for Adobe Stock or Shutterstock and only need one library"}', 'The broadest single-subscription creative library in 2026 — pick it when you need everything (video + audio + photos + templates), pick a specialist when you need depth in one category.', '{"https://help.elements.envato.com/"}', 'The February 2026 pricing restructure caps AI generations on Core and Plus tiers, which surprised long-time subscribers used to unlimited access. Asset quality varies widely — the 27M+ library includes plenty of dated or low-quality items alongside the strong material; expect to filter aggressively. Search and discovery UX is functional but lags Adobe Stock and Freepik on visual search and AI-powered relevance. Commercial licence covers most use cases but has restrictions on broadcast / film / merchandise that require reading the fine print. No native API for programmatic asset search and download.', '{}', '{"reddit_threads":[]}'::jsonb, '{"Source music, video clips, and graphics for a 30-day social-content sprint under one subscription.","Build a client website using Envato''s premium WordPress and Shopify themes.","Generate AI imagery alongside stock assets for a marketing campaign on the Plus tier.","Centralise creative-asset spend for a 10-person agency on the Teams plan."}', 'Sweet spot: a freelance designer, video editor, content creator, or small agency that touches multiple media types weekly — video this week, podcast cover art next week, presentation deck after that. Envato Elements'' breadth means one $16.50–$39/month subscription replaces what would otherwise be Storyblocks + Artlist + Adobe Stock + Envato Market piecemeal. The Teams plan at $33–35/user/month is a clean fit for agencies billing client projects.

Failure modes. First, the February 2026 AI-generation caps changed the value equation; users who joined for unlimited AI need to model the Plus or Ultimate upgrade or supplement with a dedicated AI tool (Midjourney, Ideogram). Second, asset quality variance is real — finding the keepers requires filtering and discovery time, and the library''s depth in any single category (e.g., niche-genre music) is inferior to specialists like Artlist. Third, the commercial licence is generous but not infinite — broadcast use, merchandise resale, and "end-product" licensing rules need a careful read before high-stakes campaigns.

What to pilot. Take the monthly Core plan for one production cycle (a campaign, a project, a month of social content). Track how many assets you actually use vs alternative-source costs (per-clip Storyblocks, per-track Artlist, per-image Adobe Stock). If you draw on 20+ assets across 3+ media types in a month, Elements pays for itself many times over. If you only need 2–3 assets in one category, a specialist subscription or per-item purchase is more cost-effective.', now()),
('Storyblocks', 'storyblocks', 'Subscription stock library of unlimited video, audio, and images for video creators and marketers.', 'Storyblocks is a subscription-based stock media platform that breaks the per-asset pricing model dominant in stock libraries — instead of paying $79 for a single 4K clip on Shutterstock or Pond5, Storyblocks subscribers pay a flat monthly or annual fee and download as much stock video, motion graphics, After Effects templates, audio tracks, sound effects, and stock photos as they need under a royalty-free license that covers commercial use.

The library skews toward video creators: 4K stock footage, drone aerials, lifestyle b-roll, motion backgrounds, lower-third templates, and Premiere Pro / After Effects / DaVinci Resolve project files are the strongest categories. Audio includes a respectable music library and sound effects pack, though serious music supervisors usually pair it with a dedicated music subscription. The Maker plan is the consumer-grade entry point; Business plans add a broader license, advanced contributor content, and team-friendly features.

Storyblocks'' position in 2026 is the value pick for high-volume video creators — YouTubers, agency editors, marketing teams, and educators who need 5–20 stock assets per video and would burn thousands per month on per-clip libraries. The Impact-managed affiliate program pays solid commission and converts well in creator-tooling, video-editing, and YouTube-growth audiences.', 'https://www.storyblocks.com', 'paid', '[{"plan":"Starter (Annual)","price":"$15/mo billed annually","features":["Unlimited standard-license video, audio, and images","720p and 1080p downloads","Royalty-free commercial use","Personal and small business projects"]},{"plan":"Unlimited All Access","price":"$30/mo billed annually","features":["Unlimited 4K video downloads","Full After Effects and Premiere templates","Music and sound effects","Standard royalty-free license"]},{"plan":"Business","price":"$65/mo billed annually","features":["Enterprise license (larger productions)","Unlimited downloads across all categories","Advanced contributor content","Team and brand uses"]}]'::jsonb, 'beginner', false, '{"web"}', '{"Unlimited stock video downloads (HD and 4K)","Royalty-free music library","Sound effects pack","After Effects templates","Premiere Pro project files","DaVinci Resolve templates","Stock photos and illustrations","Motion backgrounds and overlays","Browser-based search and preview","Bulk download history","Royalty-free commercial license","Brand and team-friendly Business license"}', '{"Adobe Premiere Pro","Adobe After Effects","DaVinci Resolve","Final Cut Pro","Canva","CapCut","Camtasia","Filmora"}', true, '{"YouTubers needing weekly b-roll and motion graphics","Marketing teams producing high-volume social video","Course creators sourcing visuals for lessons","Agency editors juggling multiple client projects"}', '{"Filmmakers needing exclusive or boutique footage (use Pond5 / Artgrid)","Music supervisors needing top-tier scoring (use Musicbed / Artlist)","One-off projects where a single $79 clip is cheaper than a subscription"}', 'The best value subscription stock library for high-volume video creators in 2026 — pick it when you download 5+ assets a month, skip it for one-off needs.', '{"https://www.storyblocks.com/help"}', 'Library breadth beats library depth — search returns 50 mediocre options before one perfect clip in many niches, and quality is uneven contributor-to-contributor. The 4K library has grown rapidly but still lags Artgrid / Pond5 on cinematic footage; high-end commercial productions usually need a second source. License terms differ between plans (Starter vs Unlimited vs Business) and creators occasionally trip on usage scope when scaling productions; read the license matrix before committing. Music library is functional but generic — YouTube content-ID claim risk is low but emotional range is limited.', '{}', '{"reddit_threads":[]}'::jsonb, '{"Source 10 b-roll clips for a weekly YouTube vlog without per-clip cost.","Build a brand explainer video using After Effects templates and stock motion graphics.","Score a course module with royalty-free background music across 20 lessons.","Power an agency''s social-video team with unlimited downloads across multiple client brands."}', 'Sweet spot: a video creator or small team producing 4–20 videos per month who currently pays per-clip on Shutterstock / Pond5 and is hitting hundreds per month in stock costs. Storyblocks'' unit economics flip the equation — once you download more than 3–4 clips a month, the subscription pays for itself, and the unlimited model removes the friction of "is this clip worth $79?" mid-edit.

Failure modes. First, the unlimited model can encourage lazy creative choices — downloading the first acceptable clip instead of holding out for the right one. Discipline still matters. Second, license tiers are a real trap; a freelancer producing client work above small-business scope needs the Business license, and using Starter assets in a national TV spot is a contract breach waiting to happen. Third, expect search frustration — the catalogue is enormous but discovery tools are weaker than competitors, so building your own favourites library matters.

What to pilot. Take the 7-day or annual trial. Replace your top three stock-footage sources for a month and track: hours spent searching, asset-find rate, and total monthly cost vs your per-clip baseline. If you save more than the subscription cost and find at least 70% of what you need without supplementing, the math works permanently.', now()),
('Epidemic Sound', 'epidemic-sound', 'Royalty-free music and sound effects platform with YouTube Content-ID-safe license for creators.', 'Epidemic Sound is a Stockholm-founded music licensing platform that has become the default royalty-free music source for YouTubers, podcasters, and brand video teams. The differentiator versus most stock music libraries is the license model: Epidemic owns the rights outright (artists are commissioned and paid royalties from a central pool) which means subscribers get a clean, conflict-free commercial license that explicitly covers YouTube monetisation, social media, podcasts, advertising, and broadcast — without third-party Content-ID claims, manual whitelisting, or deletion drama after a video goes viral.

The 2026 catalogue spans 50,000+ tracks and 200,000+ sound effects across nearly every genre — cinematic, hip-hop, lo-fi, corporate, EDM, indie, world, ambient — with strong tagging by mood, energy, BPM, and instrument. The Soundmatch feature analyses your video and recommends fitting tracks; Stems lets you download isolated drum / bass / melody tracks for custom mixes. Personal plans cover solo creators; Commercial plans cover brands, agencies, and broadcasters with multi-seat workspaces and broader use rights.

Epidemic Sound''s position in 2026 is the safest, cleanest music license for monetised video — Artlist competes hard on price and depth, but Epidemic''s Content-ID-safe guarantee is uniquely battle-tested at scale. The hybrid affiliate program (Impact-managed for partners plus an in-house creator referral program) is well-paid and converts strongly with YouTubers reviewing creator tools.', 'https://www.epidemicsound.com', 'paid', '[{"plan":"Personal","price":"$15.99/mo billed annually","features":["For monetised social channels","YouTube, TikTok, Instagram, podcasts","Royalty-free music and SFX","Stems and Soundmatch"]},{"plan":"Commercial","price":"$59/mo billed annually","features":["Branded content and ads","Client work and agency use","Larger team seats","Full catalogue access"]},{"plan":"Enterprise","price":"Custom","features":["Broadcast and theatrical rights","Multi-seat team workspaces","API access","Dedicated account manager"]}]'::jsonb, 'beginner', false, '{"web","mobile"}', '{"50,000+ royalty-free tracks","200,000+ sound effects","YouTube Content-ID safe license","Soundmatch (AI track recommendation from video)","Stems (isolated instrument tracks)","Mood / energy / BPM / instrument filters","Mobile apps for browsing on the go","Direct integrations with Premiere Pro and DaVinci Resolve","Curated playlists by genre and use case","Channel whitelisting for monetised YouTube channels"}', '{"Adobe Premiere Pro","DaVinci Resolve","Final Cut Pro","Adobe Audition","CapCut","YouTube","TikTok","Vimeo"}', true, '{"YouTubers running monetised channels at any scale","Podcasters needing intro music and bed scoring","Brand video teams producing social and ad content","Agency editors juggling client work that needs clean music rights"}', '{"Filmmakers needing custom-scored original compositions (hire a composer)","Top-tier theatrical or broadcast productions where uniqueness matters","Free-tier creators where any paid music subscription is over budget"}', 'The safest royalty-free music license for monetised video in 2026 — pick it when YouTube monetisation matters, skip it for hobby projects or theatrical scoring.', '{"https://www.epidemicsound.com/help/"}', 'Catalogue is huge but corporate-leaning — finding genuinely distinctive tracks for cinematic, indie, or experimental projects requires patience, and many tracks feel interchangeable. The Personal license does not cover client work or branded content — agencies and freelancers must be on Commercial regardless of revenue. Some long-time subscribers report friction when leaving the platform: tracks used in older videos must remain on Epidemic Sound''s license to retain rights, which complicates churn. Mobile app library browsing lags the desktop search experience.', '{}', '{"reddit_threads":[]}'::jsonb, '{"Score a weekly YouTube channel with rotating royalty-free tracks across 50+ episodes.","License the intro and outro music for a podcast with global distribution.","Soundtrack a brand''s social video portfolio without third-party Content-ID claims.","Build a sound-effects library for a creator''s gaming and reaction video catalogue."}', 'Sweet spot: a monetised YouTuber, podcaster, or brand video team producing weekly content where music rights matter and any Content-ID claim or strike represents lost revenue or reputation risk. Epidemic Sound''s license model is genuinely distinctive — competitors have closed the gap on catalogue and price, but the simplicity and battle-tested cleanness of the Epidemic license still justifies the premium for creators with real monetisation downside.

Failure modes. First, treating the Personal license as covering client work or branded content — it does not, and using Personal-licensed tracks in paid client deliverables is a contract violation that surfaces during audits. Second, expecting cinematic uniqueness — the catalogue is broad but lean toward broadly-licensable rather than artistically distinctive material; high-stakes brand spots may need bespoke scoring. Third, the lock-in tail — videos using Epidemic music must keep the subscription active for the videos to retain a clean license, which makes "trying it for a month" deceptively expensive long-term.

What to pilot. Subscribe for one full content cycle (4–8 weeks for most creators) and use Epidemic for every track in that period. Track time-saved versus your previous source, monetisation status of all uploaded videos, and any Content-ID claims received. If you ship more videos faster with zero claim drama, the subscription pays for itself in attention and revenue protection.', now()),
('Re:amaze', 'reamaze', 'Helpdesk, live chat, and AI chatbot platform built for ecommerce and SaaS support teams.', 'Re:amaze is a customer-support helpdesk platform owned by GoDaddy since 2021 that combines shared inbox, live chat, chatbot automation, AI-powered reply assistance, and FAQ knowledge bases into a single workspace. The product is positioned squarely at ecommerce stores and SaaS companies that need omnichannel support — email, live chat, social DMs (Facebook, Instagram, WhatsApp), SMS, and voice — without stitching together Zendesk plus Intercom plus a separate chatbot.

The 2024–2026 product line layers AI throughout: an AI assistant that drafts replies based on past conversation history, an AI chatbot trained on the support knowledge base that handles tier-1 questions autonomously, AI conversation summarisation for handoffs, and AI sentiment / intent classification for routing. Native ecommerce integrations are deeper than competitors — Shopify, BigCommerce, WooCommerce, Magento, Gorgias-style order data sidecars in the inbox showing purchase history, tracking, and refund options inline.

Re:amaze''s position in 2026 is the practical alternative to Zendesk for SMB ecommerce and SaaS — meaningfully cheaper, faster to deploy, ecommerce-aware out of the box, and with AI features baked in rather than priced as add-ons. The in-house affiliate program pays recurring commission and is well-suited for ecommerce-stack and SaaS-tooling reviewers. GoDaddy ownership has stabilised the company without disrupting product direction.', 'https://www.reamaze.com', 'paid', '[{"plan":"Basic","price":"$29/staff/mo","features":["Shared inbox across email and chat","Standard helpdesk and FAQ","Basic reporting","Live chat widget"]},{"plan":"Pro","price":"$49/staff/mo","features":["Chatbots and automation","Departments","Advanced reporting","Branding","SMS and voice channels"]},{"plan":"Plus","price":"$69/staff/mo","features":["Advanced AI features","Custom integrations","Priority support","Status page","Advanced security"]},{"plan":"Starter (Lightweight)","price":"$59/mo flat","features":["Up to 500 conversations/mo","Unlimited staff","Core helpdesk","Best for very small teams"]}]'::jsonb, 'beginner', true, '{"web","mobile","api"}', '{"Shared inbox across email, chat, social, SMS, and voice","AI reply assistant trained on past conversations","AI chatbot with knowledge-base training","Live chat widget with proactive messages","FAQ and knowledge base builder","Departments and team workflows","Macros and saved replies","Order and customer data sidebar (ecommerce)","Conversation tagging and routing rules","CSAT and NPS surveys","Status page for outage communication","Mobile apps for agents on the go"}', '{"Shopify","BigCommerce","WooCommerce","Magento","Stripe","Slack","Salesforce","HubSpot","Zapier","Mailchimp"}', true, '{"Shopify and BigCommerce stores running their own support team","SaaS companies wanting helpdesk plus chat plus chatbot in one tool","SMBs replacing Zendesk to cut costs and consolidate","Support teams of 3–25 agents handling omnichannel volume"}', '{"Enterprise support orgs with 100+ agents and complex SLAs (Zendesk wins)","Pure community-only support (use Discourse / Circle)","Solo founders under 100 conversations/month (free tools suffice)"}', 'A practical, ecommerce-aware Zendesk alternative for SMBs in 2026 — pick it when you need helpdesk plus chatbot plus AI without enterprise pricing.', '{"https://www.reamaze.com/guides"}', 'Per-staff pricing scales linearly — a 20-agent Pro team is $1,000+/month before the Plus AI add-ons. AI chatbot accuracy is good for trained scope (return policy, shipping times, password resets) but degrades fast on edge cases; expect to keep human-in-the-loop for at least 30% of tier-1 volume early on. Reporting is functional but lacks the depth of Zendesk Explore for complex ops; teams running formal QA programs will find limits. Mobile apps are stable but feature-thin compared to the web experience.', '{}', '{"reddit_threads":[]}'::jsonb, '{"Run a Shopify store''s entire support — email, chat, Instagram DMs — from one inbox.","Deploy an AI chatbot that resolves 40% of tier-1 questions before reaching a human.","Surface order and refund data inline in conversations to cut handle time.","Send proactive chat messages to customers stuck on checkout to recover abandoned carts."}', 'Sweet spot: a Shopify or BigCommerce store doing $1M–$50M GMV with a 3–25 agent support team that has outgrown Gmail-based support but doesn''t want Zendesk pricing or complexity. Re:amaze''s ecommerce-native data sidebar and bundled chatbot eliminate the typical "helpdesk + chat + bot + AI" four-vendor stack, and the per-staff pricing stays sane as the team scales.

Failure modes. The biggest is over-trusting the AI chatbot on day one — the bot needs 4–6 weeks of training data and prompt tuning before it handles even tier-1 volume reliably, and rushing it live damages CSAT. The second is treating Re:amaze as a Zendesk replacement at enterprise scale; once you have 50+ agents, complex shift schedules, formal SLAs, and integration with Workforce Management tools, Zendesk''s mature ops layer outclasses Re:amaze. Third, GoDaddy ownership has been benign so far but creates a dependency on a parent company''s strategic priorities — worth noting for multi-year commitments.

What to pilot. Migrate one channel (live chat is fastest) for 30 days, train the AI assistant on 3 months of past tickets, and measure first-response time, resolution time, CSAT, and ticket deflection by the chatbot. If deflection clears 25% and CSAT holds, expand to email and social. If the AI is hallucinating or CSAT drops, slow the rollout and invest in macro / FAQ quality before automating further.', now()),
('LiveAgent', 'liveagent', 'Multi-channel helpdesk with live chat, call center, ticketing, and AI assistant for support teams.', 'LiveAgent is a long-running customer-support platform from Quality Unit (Slovakia) that bundles ticketing, live chat, call center, social-media support, and a knowledge base into a single multichannel helpdesk. The product''s pitch is breadth-per-dollar: instead of paying separately for Zendesk + Aircall + Intercom + a chatbot, LiveAgent offers all five capabilities in one subscription, with feature parity good enough for most SMB and mid-market support orgs.

The 2024–2026 product line adds an AI Assistant that drafts replies, summarises long threads, suggests knowledge-base articles, and translates inbound messages across 40+ languages. The native call center is a real differentiator — most helpdesk competitors require Aircall or Talkdesk integrations for phone support, while LiveAgent has built-in IVR, call recording, queues, and transfers. Live chat includes proactive messages, real-time visitor tracking, and a chat-button widget. Tickets unify across email, chat, calls, social DMs, and forms.

LiveAgent''s position in 2026 is the budget-conscious all-in-one for SMB support orgs — the deliberately broad coverage means individual modules trail best-in-class specialists (Aircall on voice, Intercom on chat, Zendesk on enterprise ticketing), but the consolidated bill and unified inbox are compelling for cost-sensitive teams. The in-house affiliate program pays 20% recurring commission and is widely promoted in the customer-support tools space.', 'https://www.liveagent.com', 'paid', '[{"plan":"Small","price":"$15/agent/mo","features":["Ticketing only","3 email accounts","7-day ticket history","Basic reporting"]},{"plan":"Medium","price":"$35/agent/mo","features":["Ticketing plus live chat","Unlimited history","10 email accounts","Chat satisfaction survey"]},{"plan":"Large","price":"$59/agent/mo","features":["All Medium plus call center","IVR and call recording","Unlimited integrations","Audit log"]},{"plan":"Enterprise","price":"$85/agent/mo","features":["Multi-brand support","Advanced security","Dedicated account manager","SLA management"]}]'::jsonb, 'beginner', true, '{"web","mobile","api"}', '{"Unified ticketing across email, chat, calls, social, and forms","Built-in call center with IVR, recording, and queues","Live chat widget with proactive messages","AI Assistant for reply drafting and translation","Knowledge base and customer portal","Social media support (Facebook, Instagram, X, WhatsApp)","Customer satisfaction surveys","Time tracking and SLA management","Department and team workflows","Macros and canned responses","Audit logs and reporting","Multi-brand workspaces (Enterprise)"}', '{"Shopify","WooCommerce","Magento","Salesforce","HubSpot","Slack","Mailchimp","Stripe","WordPress","Zapier"}', true, '{"SMBs wanting helpdesk plus voice plus chat in one tool","Cost-conscious support orgs of 5–50 agents","Multi-language support teams (translation features)","Companies needing native call center without Aircall add-on"}', '{"Enterprise support orgs needing best-in-class voice (Aircall / Talkdesk win)","Pure ecommerce conversational support (Gorgias / Re:amaze fit better)","Communities and forums (use Discourse)"}', 'A breadth-first multichannel helpdesk with native call center built in — pick LiveAgent when you want one bill instead of four, skip it when any single channel needs best-in-class depth.', '{"https://www.liveagent.com/academy/"}', 'UI shows its age — the interface is functional but feels less polished than Zendesk or Intercom, and onboarding takes longer than the cleaner SaaS competitors. AI Assistant is helpful for drafting but produces generic output without prompt tuning; expect 3–4 weeks of refinement before the AI matches your brand voice. Native call center quality is solid but reliability and integrations lag dedicated voice platforms — high-volume call centers may outgrow it. Per-agent pricing scales linearly and the Large tier (where most teams need to be for full features) is $59/agent/month.', '{}', '{"reddit_threads":[]}'::jsonb, '{"Consolidate Zendesk plus Aircall plus Intercom into one $59/agent helpdesk.","Run a multilingual support team with AI translation across 40+ languages.","Deploy a built-in call center with IVR and recording without a separate voice vendor.","Track SLA compliance and CSAT across email, chat, and phone in one dashboard."}', 'Sweet spot: a 5–50 agent SMB or mid-market support org running multichannel volume (email plus chat plus phone plus social) on a budget, where consolidating four vendor bills into one matters more than having best-in-class depth on any single channel. LiveAgent''s native call center is the rare differentiator — most helpdesk platforms outsource voice to Aircall or Talkdesk, so the integrated approach actually saves real money and admin overhead.

Failure modes. The biggest is buying LiveAgent when you''re actually growing into a specialist — if call volume is your dominant channel and quality matters (regulated industries, financial services, high-stakes B2B), Aircall + Zendesk will outperform LiveAgent''s built-in voice. The second is treating the AI Assistant as plug-and-play; like any AI helper it requires real training data and prompt tuning before output is brand-appropriate. Third, the UI is functional but dated — agent satisfaction is sometimes lower than newer platforms, and recruiting agents accustomed to Intercom or Front can produce friction.

What to pilot. Take the 30-day trial, migrate one channel (live chat is fastest), and run it parallel to your current stack for 4 weeks. Measure first-response time, resolution time, agent satisfaction, and CSAT. If parity holds and the consolidated bill saves 30%+ versus your current vendors, scale to the rest of your channels. If any single channel''s quality drops noticeably, keep the specialist for that channel and use LiveAgent for the rest.', now()),
('Tawk.to', 'tawk-to', 'Free live chat plus chatbot plus ticketing platform monetised via paid agents and AI add-ons.', 'Tawk.to is a live chat platform with an unusual business model: the core product (unlimited live chat, basic chatbot, ticketing, knowledge base, multi-agent inbox) is genuinely free forever, with no message limits, no contact limits, and no expiring trial. Monetisation comes from optional paid add-ons — hired chat agents from Tawk.to''s pool ($1/hour), AI Assist add-on, branding removal, video chat, and SMS. This model has driven enormous distribution: Tawk.to powers chat on millions of websites globally, claiming the largest deployed live-chat user base in the category.

The product is competent across the support stack: live chat widget with visitor monitoring, multi-agent inbox, automated triggers, canned responses, file sharing, video and voice chat, ticketing for offline messages, knowledge base builder, and a basic chatbot called Neko. The 2024–2026 AI Assist add-on layers smarter automation — AI reply drafting trained on past conversations, AI summarisation, and AI deflection bots that handle FAQs autonomously.

Tawk.to''s position in 2026 is the default zero-cost live chat for SMBs, indie SaaS, ecommerce shops, and side projects that want chat capability without a recurring bill. The free tier alone covers what competitors charge $30–50/agent/month for. The in-house monetisation flywheel (paid agents, AI add-ons, branding removal) is the affiliate-equivalent surface — Tawk.to does not run a traditional affiliate program but its viral free tier and add-on economics are how partners and reviewers drive value.', 'https://www.tawk.to', 'freemium', '[{"plan":"Free Forever","price":"$0","features":["Unlimited chats and contacts","Unlimited agents","Live chat widget","Ticketing and knowledge base","Mobile apps"]},{"plan":"Remove Branding","price":"$19/mo","features":["Removes Tawk.to branding from chat widget","All free features included"]},{"plan":"AI Assist","price":"$29/mo","features":["AI reply drafting","AI conversation summaries","AI knowledge-base bot","Trained on past conversations"]},{"plan":"Hired Chat Agent","price":"$1/hour","features":["Tawk.to-staffed agent answering your chat","24/7 availability options","English-speaking agents","Pay only for hours used"]}]'::jsonb, 'beginner', true, '{"web","mobile","desktop","api"}', '{"Free unlimited live chat and agents","Multi-agent shared inbox","Visitor monitoring and tracking","Automated chat triggers","Canned responses and shortcuts","File sharing in chat","Video and voice chat","Ticketing for offline messages","Knowledge base builder","Basic chatbot (Neko)","AI Assist add-on (paid)","Native mobile and desktop apps","45+ language support"}', '{"WordPress","Shopify","Wix","Squarespace","Magento","Joomla","Drupal","Zapier","Webflow","Slack"}', true, '{"SMBs and indie SaaS wanting free live chat without compromise","Ecommerce stores adding chat as a low-risk experiment","Side projects and bootstrapped businesses on zero budget","Multilingual sites needing 45+ language support"}', '{"Enterprise support orgs needing SLA, audit logs, advanced security (Zendesk wins)","Teams that need polished modern UX over feature breadth (Intercom fits better)"}', 'The dominant free live chat platform globally in 2026 — pick Tawk.to when budget is zero and feature breadth matters, skip it when polished UX or enterprise features are non-negotiable.', '{"https://help.tawk.to/"}', 'The free tier comes with the Tawk.to-branded widget by default — removing branding requires the $19/month add-on, which several SMBs find a soft up-sell. UI feels dated compared to Intercom or Crisp; modern teams accustomed to clean SaaS interfaces will notice. AI Assist add-on is competent but trails dedicated AI helpdesk tools (Re:amaze, Intercom Fin) in accuracy and training depth. Hired-agent quality varies — paid agents are Tawk.to-staffed generalists, not your trained team, so handoff to your own staff for non-trivial questions is essential. Reporting is basic versus Zendesk Explore.', '{}', '{"reddit_threads":[]}'::jsonb, '{"Add free live chat to a Shopify store without monthly cost.","Run multilingual customer support across 45+ languages on a global ecommerce site.","Deploy a knowledge-base bot that deflects 30% of tier-1 chat questions autonomously.","Hire $1/hour Tawk.to agents to staff overnight chat coverage on a small team."}', 'Sweet spot: an SMB, ecommerce store, or indie SaaS that wants to add live chat as a customer-acquisition or support channel without committing to a $30–50/agent/month subscription. Tawk.to''s free tier is genuinely usable at scale — millions of sites prove this — and the optional paid add-ons (branding removal, AI Assist, hired agents) let teams scale spending only when value is proven.

Failure modes. The biggest is treating Tawk.to as enterprise-grade when it isn''t — audit logs, advanced SLA management, role-based access controls, and compliance certifications are thinner than Zendesk or Intercom, and regulated industries will hit walls. The second is over-relying on hired agents — they fill coverage gaps but lack product knowledge, so escalation paths to your team must be tight. Third, the dated UI and free-tier branding make Tawk.to a less prestigious choice for high-end brand sites where chat polish reflects on brand quality.

What to pilot. Install the free widget on your site for 30 days and measure chat volume, conversion lift on chat-engaged visitors, and CSAT from chat respondents. If chat drives meaningful conversion lift or deflects support email volume, the value is real; consider whether the free tier suffices long-term or whether AI Assist and branding removal are worth $48/month combined. If chat volume is low or conversions don''t lift, the bottleneck is product-page UX or traffic quality, not the chat tool.', now()) ON CONFLICT (slug) DO NOTHING;
